title: cheesy breakfast casserole(breakfast)
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread cubes in dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together the next 7 ingredients and pour evenly over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours, covered.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake casserole, uncovered, until set, about 1 hour.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Note:
Use in salads, pasta or with meat.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, creamed corn, corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add granulated sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well after each one.
Sift flour and baking powder; add with coconut oil, vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti and ground meat sauce
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion and bell pepper.
When done, add garlic salt, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add tomato sauce. Add water.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: company chicken
directions: Split chicken breasts.
Wrap each in a bacon strip.
Cover the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with shredded, chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top of beef.
Blend sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, edge pan with parsley.
(May be refrigerated up to 2 days now.)
Bake uncovered at 250° for 3 hours.
(Do not refrigerate covered with aluminum foil because of mushroom soup.)

title: turkey and rice casserole(low-fat)
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; set aside.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with rotary beater.
Add next 4 ingredients, then beat in milk.
Place in pie shell.
Bake first 15 minutes at 450°, next 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 1 gallon iced tea with lemon
directions: Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
(Do not allow water to boil for it produces bitter taste.)
Steep 1/2 hour.
Squeeze bags and discard them.
Stir in one packet Kool-Aid lemonade.
Add 3 1/2 quarts cold water.

title: oriental green beans
directions: In medium saucepan, combine beans, salt and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cook until tender and drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
In large skillet, cook celery and mushrooms in oil until celery is tender-crisp.
Combine reserved liquid with cornstarch, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Stir into celery mixture.
Add beans.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in almonds.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll the cheese ball in 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add syrup and melted candy bars.
Add salt to flour, stir soda into buttermilk and add to other ingredients, alternating with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Let rise, then mix with the other ingredients.
Place in warm area.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into desired size.
Place in muffin tin.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes.
Yields 25 rolls.

title: citrus pork chops
directions: Trim fat and arrange in baking pan.
Salt and pepper chops. Mix balance of ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Sauce is also good on chicken.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour and add to eggs.
Stir in lemon juice and pineapple or apricot juice.
Mix well.
Place mixture in double boiler and stir often until thick.
Cool; refrigerate.
Keeps 3 to 4 weeks.
Mix with thawed whipped topping and serve over salad or mix with fruit salad.

title: corn belt chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Brown onion in fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes or so.
Crumble bacon on top when serving.

title: 3 bean chili chowder
directions: Go home and put the meaty bones in your biggest pot.
Pour on the beef broth and heat to a boil.
Add salt and pepper, a dash of paprika and any other spices your family likes.
Peel and cut up the vegetables.
Add to the boiling soup, then lower the heat to simmer for 45 minutes.
Add pasta and stir as it gets tender. Serve with crusty rolls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients up to vanilla only.
Beat well on low.
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue mixing; scrape sides often.
Stir in nuts by hand.
Add coconut by hand also.
Grease loaf pan.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, nuts, bananas and strawberries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil, then boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips until well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
If desired, decorate with more nuts.
Chill; cut into squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds fudge.

title: sausage broccoli casserole
directions: Place peeled potatoes and remaining vegetables in a bowl and mix spices in oil.
Coat vegetables with oil mixture.
Place all in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a heavy skillet until tender. Add soups, green chiles and broth, mixing well. Layer half the tortilla pieces in a 13 x 9 baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray. Layer chicken, cheese and remaining tortilla pieces on top. Pour on soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, salt, water and margarine.
Cook until almost dry, about 15 minutes.
Add soup, milk, cheese and rice.
Cook until cheese melts.
Put into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with crackers or bread crumbs.
(May used canned French fried onion rings instead of bread crumbs.)
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: beef goulash
directions: Heat drippings in a 2-quart casserole with microwave for 20 to 30 seconds.
Add onions, potatoes and paprika.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add meat, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add a small amount of the water to cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch dissolves.
Add cornstarch mixture and remaining water to casserole.
Cover and cook 12 to 14 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: skillet pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet and pour off fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add soup, water, celery and thyme.
Simmer 30 minutes. Stir in 1/2 cup rice.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together and shape into patties.
Fry in oil on very low heat until golden brown.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine milk, margarine, cocoa and sugar.
Bring to boil and let boil for 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: green tomato raspberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan on stove and boil for 20 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: no bake cream cake
directions: Melt chocolate, marshmallows and milk (let cool completely). Mix in Cool Whip.
Slice cake into layer, one or two.
Spread some of mixture on each layer.
Frost cake with rest of mixture.
Use nuts, candies and berries for decorations.

title: tequila shrimp
directions: Flour shrimp lightly.
Add enough oil to heated skillet to cover bottom.
Saute shrimp 1/2 minute on each side.
Add pepper and tomato and cook another minute.
Add tequila and flame.
When flame subsides, add lime juice and simmer for 1 minute.
Stir in butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot cooked white rice.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter in large saucepan for 5 to 8 minutes, until onions are pale gold in color.
Drain liquid from clams into pan.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes, until the potatoes are nearly tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add clams, milk and cream.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes to heat through.
Add last tablespoon of butter and stir until melted.
Serve hot, sprinkled with paprika, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix the instant coffee and boiling water. Set aside to cool. Mix the sugar and 2 cups water.
Add to coffee mixture. Add the vodka and split vanilla bean. Allow to age for 3 weeks.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark and chocolate chips together.
Stir in peanuts. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Helpful Hint:
Soften cream cheese in a microwave for 15 to 20 seconds.

title: tuna casserole(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Boil noodles. While boiling, saute onion, pepper and pimentos in oil. Add flour, soups and milk; bring to boil, then simmer until smooth. Take off heat and add tuna and lemon juice. Pour noodles and sauce in buttered casserole dish. Mix well; top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: randy's paella rice
directions: Saut the peppers, onions and garlic, but don't brown.
Add the tomatoes, salt and broth.
Bring to a boil, then add rice, stir. Bring back to a boil, then lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
(Do not lift cover, before 20 minutes.)
Stir well and serve.
Serve with chicken, seafood or a Mexican dinner.

title: divinity
directions: Place in pan over low heat and stir constantly until sugar is dissolved. Cook, without stirring, until it reaches 252° or small amount forms soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and pour in a fine stream into the stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup nuts (optional). Drop from spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make
cake
by directions on box, using milk instead of water. Bake
in
an oblong baking pan.
Remove from oven when done
and poke
holes
in cake with big fork.
Heat pineapple with
sugar to
just boiling.
Pour over warm cake.
Let cool completely.
Mix softened cream cheese with package of vanilla pudding
and add milk.
Pour over cake.
Let sit in refrigerator
for a few minutes.
Pudding will set.
Slice bananas over top.
Spread
all over with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, cherries and coconut.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix soups; add milk and heat on stove.
Add some cubed cheese.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Bake for 35 or 40 minutes at 350°.
Crush some potato chips and put on top.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until the mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and stir just enough to hold dough together.
Place dough on board which has been dusted with flour.
Knead lightly several times.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Mix diced vegetables, Soyameat, rice and mushrooms in a 2-quart casserole; set aside.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and sprinkle jello powder over cottage cheese mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Can also use coconut on top if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix apples, grapes, celery, pecans, strawberries and yogurt in a large bowl. If you need a little more liquid, add some cran-grape juice.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix everything together, except the brown sugar.
Pour 1/2 batter into Bundt pan.
Pour remaining batter into pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cassie's potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice margarine over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and replace in oven to melt cheese.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple juice together.
Add fruit and mix. Add Cool Whip and mix.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: mex-tex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice and salt. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in another bowl.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture; mix well. Add nuts.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pans, then wrap with plastic wrap.

title: baby food salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and pineapple in a saucepan. Stir and simmer until Jell-O is melted. Remove from heat. Add baby food. Place in large bowl in refrigerator until partially set. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together in a bowl. Add to Jell-O mixture. Stir together thoroughly.
Refrigerate until it sets up like Jell-O.

title: low-cal green beans and tomatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and paprika.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes. Add the beans and simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes. Season to taste and serve.

title: coconut fruit dip
directions: In a blender, combine first 4 ingredients; cover and process for 1 minute or until smooth. Serve with fruit. Store in the refrigerator. Makes 2 cups.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, margarine and peanut butter.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate 2 hours to overnight.
In double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate.
Stick toothpick in each ball and dip into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper until hardened to the touch.
Makes about 120 balls.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Mix together the sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly at medium heat until it spins a thread.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Sift in dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts. Using plastic wrap, roll into 3 or 4 logs; flatten ends.
Wrap and chill well.
Slice 1/4-inch thick with sharp knife.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and sugar with boiling water; let cool but not jell.
Add remaining ingredients; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix and roll. Add butter, cinnamon and brown sugar. Cut into rolls. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: shortcake special
directions: Put strawberries into dessert shells and add whipping cream on top.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread, spread with butter and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together.
Pour over cheese. Cover casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Blend all ingredients lightly in large bowl; wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Roll mixture, 1 teaspoon at a time, into balls.
Roll in flour and brown evenly in oil until done.
Drain on paper towel.

title: steak and foil dinner
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece of heavy foil in baking pan; place meat on foil.
Season as desired.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion mix.
Spread 1/2 evenly on meat.
Top meat with vegetables; sprinkle water on vegetables.
Add remaining mushroom soup mix over vegetables; fold foil over and seal.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: knight time brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour and salt. Pour into sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 28 brownies.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Pour in bread.
Mix and cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Rinse and trim asparagus.
Place in 1 or 2 layers in a flat dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, dot with margarine.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Asparagus will be crunchy, and will not lose its color.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, water and rice.
Put into casserole dish.
Place chicken parts on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries into saucepan.
Add cornstarch and water; cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Dissolve jello and add sugar.
Add cherries, pineapple and coloring.
Let cool and add bananas and pecans.
Let cool until jello starts to jell.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Chill.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and add cut up chocolate bars and chocolate chips along with Marshmallow Whip and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is dissolved. Add nuts.
Pour into greased cake pan and mark in 1-inch squares.

title: cherry-pecan bread
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture. Beat until all is blended.
Fold in nuts and cherries.

title: kulolo(taro pudding)
directions: Line an 8-inch pan with foil and then with ti leaves.
Combine taro, milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan with ti leaves.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Steam 5 to 6 hours or cook in pressure cooker for 2 1/2 hours. Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: bacon-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and set aside caps.
Chop stems. Cook onion and chopped mushroom stems in butter until tender.
Add bread pieces.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bacon bits and cheese. Mound filling in caps.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.
Makes 15 to 20 appetizers.

title: french toast
directions: Put a little butter in pan.
Beat all ingredients until frothy.
Dip bread in the mixture and put in frying pan.
Cook until golden brown.

title: future farmer all-bran bread
directions: Heat 1 cup water to boiling point in large pan.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup sugar, cereal and salt.
In a small bowl add yeast to lukewarm water with sugar.
When first mixture has cooled to lukewarm add the yeast mixture to it.
Add eggs.
Stir well. Add flour and cover pan to rise to double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and make into rolls or loaves of bread.
Let rise again.
Bake rolls at 375° for 15 minutes.
Bake loaves at 325° for 45 minutes.
This is a sticky dough.
You may need to add flour when making into rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Turn cooked broccoli into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle cubed cheese over broccoli.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter over broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Pour the rest of melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: battered fish - deep fried
directions: Drain fish dry on paper towel and roll in seasoned flour.
Fold egg white into oil, yeast and warm water batter.
Mix fish with batter and deep fry in Crisco oil or any cooking oil.

title: sausage and wild rice
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Drain.
Prepare rice by package directions.
Drain mushrooms.
Mix together in a Pyrex baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese bubbles.

title: nickel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool until slightly set (like unbeaten egg white).
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese. Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until set.

title: caramel french toast
directions: Combine sugar, butter, and corn syrup in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Lightly toss berries in
2 tablespoons flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs one at a time.
Stir in remaining flour, sour cream, soda, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth. Fold in berries.
Spread one-half of batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half over batter.
Spread remaining batter and top with the rest of the nut mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Here is a nifty new way to make pecan turtles.
Maybe you already know.

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter in pan; spread brown sugar and butter in pan or baking dish.
Place pineapple and pecans on sugar and butter mixture.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar.
Gradually add pineapple juice and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter roundup cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crosses with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco seasoning mix. Put in pan. Top with vegetables, etc. Last layer added should be the shredded cheese. Dip and enjoy.

title: lemon, pineapple, mandarin orange mold
directions: Mix lemon jello and crushed pineapple and the juice in a cooking pot.
Mix thoroughly and cook on medium heat until it bubbles.
Add 3 cups cold water and mix well.
Refrigerate until it starts to jell.
Fold in the drained oranges and 1 cup chopped walnuts, if desired.
Fold in Cool Whip very well, so it reaches evenly around the edges.
Turn into 10 to 12 cup mold or use a Bundt pan.
Refrigerate overnight before unmolding.

title: raspberry coeur a la creme
directions: Beat the cream cheese with an electric mixer or in a food processor until smooth and fluffy.
Gradually blend in the sugar, scraping down the sides of the bowl as necessary.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In a small bowl, stir soy sauce into the cornstarch.
Stir in ginger, sugar, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Stir-fry 1/3 of chicken at a time in one tablespoon of sunflower oil.
Remove from a wok or push to side.
Stir soy mixture and broth into chicken. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and serve over rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickled corn
directions: Clean corn and put in crock, as many as desired.
Mix enough water and salt to cover corn.
Let set 15 days.
Cut off cob and heat.
Put in jars.
Cover with hot water and seal.

title: polish pierogies
directions: Beat together eggs and water; add mixture to flour and salt. Mix with hand to form dough. Roll out flat. Take a circle cookie cutter or a glass (upside down) to cut out dough circles.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt butter and add to scalded milk.
Next, add sugar and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs, potatoes, yeast and flour.
You have almost enough flour when it is hard to stir. Turn it out on a board and beat it with your hands.
Add flour until dough will not stick to board.
This may be put in a bowl to rise and store in refrigerator for further use.
If used at once, let dough rise in bowl until double in bulk.
Roll out, place on baking sheet and let rise again until light.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Bring soup to a boil and add lemon jello.
Combine cottage cheese, mayonnaise, celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix and fold into soup mixture.
Pour into dish and refrigerate.

title: hot fruit
directions: Showing kindness to an aged person.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Do not brown.
Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed Fritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linguini tuna salad
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile in large bowl combine remaining ingredients except tuna, peas and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Add hot linguini; toss.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce garnished as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lite luncheon salad
directions: Cook macaroni, rinse and drain.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cheese and lettuce.
Mix well.
Cover, chill to blend flavors.
Just before serving, cut 8 slices of cheese into small pieces.
Cut 4 slices diagonally into quarters.
Fold cheese pieces into salad.
Serve on lettuce and top with cheese quarters.
Cover and refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8.

title: cheese rings
directions: Cream together the butter and grated cheese.
Add the flour, mixing with your hand to make a smooth dough.
Separate into 2 parts and roll each part about 1/4 inch thick.
You may need to use a small amount of flour to do this.
Spread each piece with apple jelly and sprinkle with half of the nuts.
Roll up jelly roll fashion tightly.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice about 1/4 inch thick and bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
These rings are super with tea or with drinks.
They should be kept in a tin for at least a week before using.
They are better the longer they are kept.
I usually make a double batch for "nibblers."

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order written.
Make into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: terrik's favorite shrimp scampi
directions: Remove shell from raw shrimp.
Split to butterfly and remove vein.
Combine remaining ingredients and dip shrimp in mixture. Place in broiler pan and pour rest of mixture over.
Place under broiler in bottom of oven for 15 minutes. Allow 1 pound shrimp per 2 people.
Recipe doubles easily. Serve over pasta or lemon rice.

title: shrimp samantha
directions: In large skillet, melt butter on medium-high heat.
Cook mushrooms, onion, scallions and garlic until soft, but not brown. Add shrimp and sausage.
Cook 4 minutes longer.
Add wine.
Simmer briefly until everything is cooked through.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
You can leave in bowl or make into a ball.
Great with round crackers or vegetables.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chili mix, soup and beans (undrained).
Mix together and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: granny rainwater's lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler until thick. Pour into 2 partially cooked pie crusts.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt the bark.
Stir in the peanuts.

title: green chili corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: split pea soup(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Simmer ham for 1 hour. Add all ingredients and simmer for another hour until cooked.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Combine with next 5 ingredients.
Add soups and soy sauce.
Put in casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles on top just before serving.

title: dove or quail
directions: Clean birds and split them down the back.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in bacon drippings in a heavy skillet for 20 minutes, turning frequently.
Add lemon juice and water; cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until tender.
Baste frequently during baking, adding water, if necessary, to prevent sticking to the pan.
Serves 2.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini and onion and add salt.
Set overnight and drain.

title: easy brownies new england style
directions: Melt butter and chocolate squares slowly.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add salt and baking powder.
Stir in flour a little at a time until smooth. Add nuts.
Pour into greased and lightly floured pan.
Top with more nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: big buns potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes. Combine them with all ingredients except cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Put into 3-quart buttered casserole. Combine cornflakes and melted butter; sprinkle on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy mock cheesecake
directions: Layer whole graham crackers in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Combine Cool Whip, vanilla pudding, 1/2 the amount of milk called for on box of pudding and vanilla extract.
Make several layers of grahams and mixture.
Top with pie filling. Great doubled.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Line a 15 x 10 inch jellyroll pan with aluminum foil.
Coat foil with vegetable cooking spray.
Toss together sweet potato and 1 tablespoon oil in a pan.
Bake at 450 degrees for 35 minutes or until tender.
Whisk together remaining 1 tablespoon oil, honey, and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add sweet potato; toss well. Cool.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peasant chicken
directions: In bottom of a large Dutch oven, heat oil and brown chicken, a few pieces at a time, removing as browned.
Brown onions and bacon, then return chicken.
Pour brandy over and ignite.
Keep it burning as long as possible.
Add tomatoes, carrots, garlic, herbs and wine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; let simmer for 1 hour.

title: friendship tea(used at altrusa bazaar)
directions: Mix well; store dry in container.
Use about 1 rounded teaspoonful mix to each cup tea or more if stronger tea desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter, beat well.
Fold Cool Whip into peanut butter mixture. Pour in graham cracker crust.

title: punch slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Scrape with ice cream scoop.
Add to any clear beverage for a refreshing drink.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use one large loaf pan or two small.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grate cheese and combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well with hands.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Combine hamburger, onion and pepper. Brown in 12-inch skillet; drain fat and add beef broth, potatoes and carrots. Stir and simmer 45 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach to directions on box and squeeze out water.
Beat eggs.
Melt butter; stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in spinach.
Fold in cheeses, salt and pepper.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly in 350° oven for glass pan and 375° for metal pan.

title: nut bread(this recipe is over 60 years old)
directions: Grease and flour 1 large size loaf pan.
Add a little of the flour to the chopped nuts to keep them from sinking to the bottom. Beat yolks and whites separately.
Slowly add the sugar, milk and vanilla to the yolks.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and then the beaten egg whites.
Makes 1 large size loaf pan.
Let stand in pan 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon honey scones
directions: Stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in eggs, milk and honey until mixture is moistened. (Dough will be sticky.)
On an ungreased baking sheet, pat dough with lightly floured fingers to a 6-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add canned pumpkin.
Beat well.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, ginger and salt and beat well.
Add milk; mix well.
Bake 10 minutes in hot oven (425°) and then bake in moderate slow oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: sausage corn chowder
directions: Cook sausage in a medium saucepan.
Combine soup, milk, onions, corn and cooked sausage.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
After 5 minutes, add cheese and hot sauce. Cook until cheese has melted.

title: chicken or meat marinade
directions: In food processor, chop orange (peel and all).
Add ginger and garlic.
Chop fine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Marinate chicken or meat 30 minutes to an hour before cooking. Great for the grill!

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: In blender, blend everything, except the Colby cheese.
After the cream cheese mixture is blended, grate Colby cheese. Stir in Colby cheese with the cream cheese mixture.
Form into a ball. Roll in mixture of chili powder, paprika (small amount), parsley flakes and nuts.

title: chicken 'n cheese 'n stuffing
directions: Grease casserole or baking dish.
Lay chicken in bottom and cover with layers of Swiss cheese.
Pour soup over cheese.
(Do not add water to soup.)

title: country style steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and salt and pepper mixture thoroughly. Place steak in pan with hot oil; brown both sides.
Simmer for 20 minutes with lid on.
Add all remaining flour to pan.
Scrape dish off in pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer an additional length of time (10 minutes).
Gravy will thicken and lumps will come out as stirred.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage and brown in oil.
Add onions, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook 5 minutes, then add zucchini, tomatoes, bouillon and cabbage and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans and spaghetti and cook 20 minutes.
(Noodles should be soft.)

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together with hands.
Form into tiny balls, size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on cookie sheets.
Serve warm or cold.
May freeze for later use after cooking.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
This recipe keeps well.

title: hoowey-goowey butter bars
directions: Combine mix, eggs, melted oleo and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jarrett house biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour; once moisten with milk.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow krispy korn
directions: Combine popcorn and cereal in a large greased bowl.

title: vodka slush
directions: Boil and let cool first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in a 2-quart container.
Spoon into a 6 or 8 ounce glass, 3/4 full.
Then add 7-Up to fill glass.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Place foil over edges of crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes longer or until set.
Let cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Mix and heat either soup with green beans and pour into a casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, including beef, if desired, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Season to taste.

title: tangy lemon-lime chicken
directions: In large bowl, mix together lemon juice, lime juice, garlic, thyme, pepper, oregano and wine.
Add chicken, turning to coat. Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade. In large baking pan, arrange chicken in single layer; pour marinade over chicken.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 40 minutes, basting every 10 minutes with pan juices. To serve, arrange chicken on platter.
Spoon juices over chicken; garnish with cherry tomatoes and lemon twists.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: *Mother uses Stove Top.
Cook first and be own judge as to how much to use, might not need all of it.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook until thickened.
Pour over sliced sweet potatoes and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: delta queen corn bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Stir in corn meal.
Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture; blend.
Stir in shortening. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: matchiolli - rima's and wanda's
directions: Boil Matchiolli until done.
Prepare sauce with meat (optional), onion and bell pepper.
In a casserole dish, alternate layers of Matchiolli, Mozzarella, Cheddar and sauce.
Bake in medium-high oven for 20 minutes or until cheeses melt.
Remove from oven; garnish top with Parmesan cheese.

title: microwave crunchy caramel corn
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and nuts.
In 4-cup microwave-safe measuring cup, combine brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds to 2 minutes or until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda. (Mixture will become foamy.)
Pour over popcorn mixture and toss to coat.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Add kidney beans, diced tomatoes and chili mix.
Season to taste with chili powder. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: candy reese's cups
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll into small balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips. Dip chilled peanut butter balls in chocolate mix.
Lay on waxed paper.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Wash the eggplant thoroughly; if the skin is tough, peel it. If not, leave the peeling on; it's better that way.
Slice the eggplant into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Spread a thin coating of Miracle Whip on both sides and then dip the slices in corn meal. In a heavy skillet, heat 1 inch of oil until water pops when dropped in.
Fry the slices until they are crispy and golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Drizzle with pineapple juice.
Spread 1/3 pudding mix over bottom layer of cake, top with second layer; repeat layering ending with pudding. Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted sliced almonds and garnish with pineapple slices.
Serves 12 people.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs and add brown sugar.
Mix in Bisquick, vanilla and pecans and bake in 375° oven until brown on top and it doesn't feel soft.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add one at a time the 4 eggs.
Combine soda, dissolved in hot water.
Add salt to plain flour; add alternately to sugar mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in lemon extract.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix pecans and egg whites until pecans are sticky.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Add to nuts and stir until well coated. Spread thinly in shallow pan.
Bake stirring occasionally at 225° until dry but not brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Melt cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes; combine with meat.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter melts.
Pour slowly over corn flakes until all are coated.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and beat with electric hand mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, butter, cocoa and sugar together for 1 minute. Remove from stove and add the oatmeal, salt, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of a quarter.
Brown on all sides in dry skillet; drain on paper towels.

title: hot sausage appetizers
directions: Mix well.
Spoon into greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 mins or until golden.

title: cheesecake filling(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in butter and orange extract.
Turn mixture into spring-form pan and bake 15 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cut in Crisco and margarine.
Add buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture. Knead lightly.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° for about 10 to 12 minutes, or put biscuits on greased cookie sheet, cover and freeze.
The night before you need them, uncover and place in cold oven.
Let biscuits rise overnight.
They'll be ready to bake the next morning.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with carrots.
Add nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 X 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: brian bunce's cheesecake
directions: Mix well; no lumps.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine squash and egg; stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and cheese; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion; stir until blended.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice.
Cube Velveeta.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbled bacon and sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder. Spread on the bottom of pie pan (9-inch).
Spread pizza sauce on top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, pepper and onion.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Dip with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread on party rye or crackers.
Serve hot.

title: aunt theresa's coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and flour, 1/2 cup at a time. Add baking powder; add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix chicken soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Pour crushed crackers over mixture.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then put in refrigerator.
Before you serve this, form into two logs and roll in nuts.

title: chicken divan
directions: This can be served over rice.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons catsup. Combine ground beef, eggs, oats, soup mix and remaining catsup.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Top with remaining catsup. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 6 hours).
Use a 5-quart crock-pot.

title: cheez-its salad
directions: Combine Cheez-Its and oleo; spread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Combine milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Add mashed strawberries.
Pour into two prepared graham cracker pie crusts.
Freeze.
Take out about 30 minutes before serving.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast.
Add onion soup.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook 1 hour.
Remove meat and vegetables.
Thicken gravy with mixture of 1/4 cup flour and water.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: red leaf salad with honey vinaigrette
directions: Combine vinegar, honey and mustard in screw-top jar and shake to mix well, making Honey Vinaigrette.
Place orange, apple and cucumber in bowl of Honey Vinaigrette while preparing lettuce. Pour off vinaigrette into a jar.
Toss fruit and cucumber with lettuce.
Serve with Honey Vinaigrette.
Or divide lettuce, fruit and cucumber among 4 salad bowls and serve with Honey Vinaigrette and nuts.

title: gooey bars
directions: You can buy Morrison's Bis-Kits mix at Albertson's or you may use 1 1/8 cup Bisquick.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: one step farm house stewed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in large pot.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Blend in flour; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Add mushrooms, rice, consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased sheet pan.
Then shake 1 box dry yellow mix and 1 cup pecan pieces over top.
Melt 2 sticks butter and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: meat loaf supper
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together and form into a loaf. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Surround meat loaf with carrots, potatoes and onions.
Place the 2 bacon slices on top of the meat loaf.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and brown sugar; save 1/2 cup to put on top. Combine egg, hot water, Old Barrell and soda.
Put on bottom of pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls. Bake in moderate oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: appetizer
directions: Place half of the uncooked rolls in the bottom of a small square pan.
Place the cheese on top of the dough and pour the praline mustard glaze over the cheese.
Place almonds on top of the glaze.
Take remaining dough and wrap over the cheese, making a shell.
Place in preheated 325° oven and bake for approximately 20 minutes or until roll dough is brown.

title: ruth's quick lunch
directions: Season hamburger meat and make round balls.
Place in a baking dish lined with foil and add sliced potatoes, onions and carrots. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and seasoning.
Cover with foil and cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: new mexico enchiladas
directions: Cut round steak into small cube pieces; brown until done and add salt, ground oregano and garlic powder.
Add sauce to meat; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: ina's meat loaf
directions: Mix all
the
ingredients in a bowl, then shape it in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix jello and hot water well.
Add mayonnaise and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Crumble corned beef and mix well.
Pour into greased large Corning Ware pan and refrigerate until firm. Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar and flour.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cook at 250° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread half of mixture over crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour over crust and cream cheese and Cool Whip in dish.
Let set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture. Top with chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: mother's pea salad
directions: On amounts, use your own judgement.
Let set overnight.

title: blackberry jam
directions: `Put blackberries in a preserving kettle and cook until they are heated through.
Divide in half and put half the berries through sieve.
Return sieved berries to the kettle with whole berries and add sugar, mandarin juice, lemon juice and mandarin peel.
Stir mixture over high heat until it comes slowly to a rolling boil.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in liquid pectin, skim foam off with a metal spoon, stirring to prevent fruit from floating.
Quickly ladle into hot, sterilized jars to 1/8-inch from top and seal immediately.

title: kings arms tavern sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook sweet potatoes in boiling salted water until done; peel and mash. Stir in all of remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Turn mixture into prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and then baked when needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini microwave delite
directions: Cut each zucchini lengthwise into halves, then quarters.
In 13 x 9-inch microwave dish or platter, place and stagger each quartered piece.
Spread olive oil on each piece; sprinkle onion and garlic powders, oregano and cheese on each piece.
Cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
(Allow 30 seconds for each quarter zucchini.)

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix in order given leaving blueberries to fold in last.
Put in medium paper cups in muffin tins.
Bake in 375° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 18 medium size muffins.
Dust with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: "no bake" baked beans
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in a large iron skillet in small amount of bacon drippings until tender.
Add drained beans and all other ingredients.
Cook on low to medium heat for about 30 minutes.

title: lobster
directions: Bring kettle of water to full boiling point.
Add salt.
Add whole potato (unpeeled), onion (cut up) into quarters.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add haddock (it will go to the bottom of the kettle). Add lemon juice.
Boil until haddock rises to the top of the water.
Remove haddock - it is ready to eat.
Serve with butter or as you would any lobster.
Potato and onion edible too!

title: eric's french toast
directions: Wash your hands.
Don't wake up dad.
Crack eggs into bowl. Add a little bit of the milk and stir with a wire whisk.
Ask mom to preheat the griddle.
Add the rest of the milk and vanilla. Dip bread in the mixture and throw on the griddle.
Go watch cartoons.
Mom will do the flipping when brown.
Heat syrup in microwave.
Put butter and syrup on and wake up dad.
Yum yum!

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Place wafers in paper cups.
Mix the rest of ingredients until light and fluffy.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Dab with your favorite pie filling (optional).

title: pecan-cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar until fluffy. Blend in other ingredients and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash chilies, remove seeds and pat dry.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/2 the chilies, 1/2 the cheeses. Repeat layer, saving 1/2 cup cheeses for top.
Beat eggs. Add flour and milk until blended.
Pour egg mixture over chilies and cheese.
Casserole can be refrigerated at this point, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Spread tomato sauce evenly over top. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes more. Cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, pudding mix and water in a mixing bowl.
Pour batter in greased and floured round cake pans.	Bake at 350° until done according to package directions.
Cool.	Split each layer in half.
Mix together sour cream, sugar and coconut, blend well.
Set aside one cup.
Spread the remainder between the layers of the cake.
Add the one cup of filling to the Cool Whip. Use this to frost top and sides.
Sprinkle with extra coconut and refrigerate 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: pepper herb cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese in small pieces.
Sprinkle dry mix over and mix well.
(May be a little sticky.
Set in refrigerator for a few minutes if it is.)
Then shape into a ball.
Roll in coarse black pepper.

title: john's favorite sausage-n-beer
directions: Prick sausage all over with fork.
Cook in large skillet, turning occasionally, until brown.
Remove sausage to drain on paper towel.

title: peanut butter bar
directions: Melt together in large pan the oleo and peanut butter. Mix in powdered sugar, brown sugar and vanilla (this gets very stiff and will need to be mixed by hand). Put evenly on cookie sheet.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix lightly, but well.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together, mixing thoroughly.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: little frozen charlotte russe
directions: You also need 24 four-ounce plastic cups, roll of clear plastic wrap and candy garnishes (optional).

title: calico beans(baked beans)
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onions.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Drain, then melt cheese.
Stir in butter, then cream of mushroom.
Stir all together, then sprinkle white bread in and 1/2 package of Town House crackers and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Stir all together.
Put in cake pan for 30 minutes.
If you want to, you can take another 1/2 package of Town House crackers and sprinkle over top of casserole and bake all together.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Cook remaining ingredients 5 minutes and then pour over drained carrots.
Chill and serve.

title: last minute casserole
directions: Cut meat into small cubes.
Combine with soup, peas and carrots and 2 cups noodles in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High, covered, for 6 to 7 minutes.
Stir 1/2 way through and at the end.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes; top with remaining 1/2 cup noodles.

title: hot chipped beef
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sifted flour, baking powder and salt mix together.
Roll dough on floured board; cut into desired shape. Fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and canning salt.
Cover with ice, let set 3 hours.
Drain juice from cucumbers.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
Boil another 5 minutes. Pack in hot sterilized jars; seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with the melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (save enough of mixture to sprinkle on top).
Press the ice cream over the cookie base.
Cover the ice cream with the fudge topping.
Cover the fudge topping with Cool Whip.
Top the dessert with the remaining cookie mixture.
You may add nuts anywhere you want to.
This dessert can be made ahead of time and refrozen until served.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into jelly roll or pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Top with 3 to 4 cups finely chopped vegetables:
tomatoes, green peppers, red peppers, green onions, black olives, broccoli, cauliflower, shredded carrots, parsley, chives, radishes.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar or Longhorn cheese, not too heavy so colors of veggies show through. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into hor d'oeuvre-size pieces.

title: chicken breast saute and new potatoes
directions: In hot butter in large skillet, brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir in bouillon cube dissolved in the hot water.
Pour over browned chicken.
Cook slowly, covered, about 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add drained white potatoes and wine.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in milk and water, then add vanilla.

title: alpine chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth. Serves 2.

title: lemon crumbles
directions: Put half of mixture on top and half on bottom.
Fill with lemon; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
When done, drain off fat.
Add tomato paste, water, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Put lid on and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: cuke marinated pickles
directions: Use large container.
Use slender cukes, sliced thinly, crosswise.
Do not peel. Slice bell peppers in approximately 1/2-inch slices.
Cut in halves.
Put ingredients in container as in the order listed.
Do not mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Stir or mix after marinating time.
May be put in jars. Keep in refrigerator.

title: esther pedigo's hawaiian chess pie
directions: Combine all but pineapple and coconut.
Beat until smooth. Add pineapple and coconut.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with cornbread dressing.
Place 1/2 of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan; spread over bottom.
Put chicken (chopped) over dressing.
Mix sour cream and soup together and spread over chicken.
Spread remaining crumbs over top.
Pour 1 cup or more of hot chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes, or until fluffy.

title: hamburger-sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown and crumble hamburger and sausage; drain fat.
Cut cheese into chunks and add to skillet.
Stir until melted; add seasonings.
Spread on party rye bread (you will use almost the whole package).
Place on cookie sheets.
Place under broiler, not on the nearest rack.
Broil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Watch, because they brown quickly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Fill onion soup can with mushroom juice and water chestnut juice and finish filling with water; add to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: savory pork rolls
directions: Trim fat and remove bones from steaks.
Pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Stir egg and milk into bread crumbs. Add onion, mustard, poultry seasoning and salt.
Mix well. Divide stuffing between steaks.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Coat with flour and brown in shortening. Remove to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Discard excess fat from skillet. Add water to drippings.
Pour over rolls and bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve with Mushroom Sauce.

title: terry's bbq sauce
directions: To use on
grill, add 1/4 cup more honey.
To spice up, add more red and black pepper.

title: baked spinach casserole
directions: Mix well first 7 ingredients in order given in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until set and lightly browned.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add 1 cup flour at a time.
Beat well after each.
Spread 3/4 of the dough on greased high-sided cookie sheet (jelly roll pan).
Spread pie filling on top.
Drop rest of dough on top by big spoonfuls.
Spread it around somewhat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice and boil potatoes. Thicken with flour mixture. Add cheeses and sour cream. Add bacon bits or have on sides. You can halve this recipe.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Add ingredients in order; stir after each addition.
Pour into large pan or large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaf with crackers.

title: sheepherder's bread dip
directions: Cut off top of bread loaf; hollow out inside.
Take insides of loaf and tear in bite pieces.
Set aside.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Mix salt with cucumbers and onions.
Let stand for 3 hours, mix occasionally.

title: aunt dee dee's pickles(no garlic pickles)
directions: Run off juice from pickles; rinse.
Slice pickles into chunks.
Boil ingredients (all but pickles).
Pour into jars; add 1 teaspoon pickling spice to each jar.
Add pickles; store in refrigerator for at least 1 week before eating.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash, onions and peppers; let set 1 hour. Cover with ice; drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to a full boil.
Pour over squash.
Put back on stove; bring to a full boil.
Pack in jars.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Whip eggs in mixer.
Add cream to eggs and whip.
Add sugar slowly to eggs and cream mixture and whip so all sugar is dissolved.
Add one can milk, vanilla and salt.
Blend thoroughly. Then add two more cans of milk.

title: fish salad(fiskesalat)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, sugar, vinegar and pickles.
Add fish, macaroni and peas to mixture.
Serve cold with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: hot crabmeat puffs(appetizer)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine softened cream cheese, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in crabmeat, almonds and onions.
Cut top off of miniature cream puffs.
Fill with crab mix and replace tops.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in an airtight container.
Mix 1 teaspoon to 1 cup hot water or to taste.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix well, serve chilled.

title: drunken pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops until browned on both sides.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Add mixture of beer, catsup and brown sugar. Let simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lemon barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend well.
May be stored in covered jar in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Remove garlic clove after 2 days.

title: best salad
directions: Mix pie filling, milk and whipped topping in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss well; refrigerate.
Will keep for several days.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Press into skillet.
Layer with tomatoes and cheese.
Cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until cooked through.

title: soley's chicken a la king
directions: Cook onion and green pepper or celery in butter until tender. Blend in soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Add chicken, pimentos and pepper.
Heat slowly about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over patty shells and sprinkle with paprika.

title: gourmet turkey soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Stir in curry powder.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, carrots, celery, broth, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in green beans, turkey, oregano and parsley.
Continue cooking 15 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Combine milk and flour; stir in gently until well blended.
The soup should be slightly thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cucumber cinnamon rings
directions: *Use cucumbers not suitable for normal pickling.
Cut cucumbers into 1/2-inch rings or sticks.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Be careful not to burn garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, chili powder, Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; stir into sauce until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover; simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggs and liver filling
directions: Combine hard-cooked eggs with minced, cooked liver.
Season with salt, pepper and prepared horseradish.
Moisten with mayonnaise.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mash the bananas with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil, then mix with jello.
Put cream cheese, baby food and Eagle Brand milk in a blender; then add jello mix.
In a bowl, drain pineapple and add chopped nuts.
Then add the mixed ingredients in blender to the pineapple and nuts.
Let set.

title: banana chocolate pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and milk in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in brown Sugar Twin and cocoa until thoroughly blended.
Fold in mashed banana and vanilla extract.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Spoon chilled pudding into dessert dishes. Garnish with banana slices.

title: apple strudel lite
directions: Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Open dough onto sheet, pressing out to make crust.
Spread apple mix evenly; roll out like a jelly roll.
Spread 8 teaspoons diet margarine on top; bake for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Serves 8.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Add milk and syrup, then add margarine.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Continue boiling, without stirring, until small amount of mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat until it thickens and loses gloss.
Turn at once into greased pan.

title: bachelor's barbecue
directions: Place roast in roasting pan (do not brown or salt).
Pour catsup and Coca-Cola over roast and scatter sliced onion over top of roast.
Cover and cook at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Sift flour before measuring.
Then add to other ingredients.
Fill 2 x 10 x 14-inch deep pan which has been well-greased and floured, half full.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with lemon sauce or lemon flavored frosting.

title: baked rice chicken
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk; mix until smooth.
Mix in rice and dried onion soup mix.
Place 1 layer of this mixture on the bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish (or one fairly big to fit chicken and sauce).
Then place chicken on top of it.
Pour the rest of the sauce over the chicken.
Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Keep an eye on your rice so it doesn't stick.)

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a medium-sized electric mixer bowl, combine baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: filled coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients and divide dough in half.
Spread half on bottom of greased pan.
Use any fresh fruit.
Cover with rest of dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: jo's corn bread
directions: Mix together egg, milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients to liquids; mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: daisy biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
With kitchen shears or knife, make 5 equally spaced 1/2-inch cuts around outer edge of each biscuit to make daisy shape.
Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet.
With thumb, make a deep indention in center of each biscuit.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon preserves into indentation in each biscuit.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 6 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar, flour and nutmeg mixture.
Add rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dot with butter.
Add top crust.
I rub small amount of butter on top crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lime cooler
directions: Blend limeade concentrate, milk and vanilla ice cream with beater or in the blender.
Pour into tall chilled glasses.
Top with 1 scoop of lime sherbet ice cream.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Heat butter and milk.
When very hot, stir in grated cheese, bread crumbs, dry mustard and cayenne.
When cheese is melted, stir in eggs.
Serve on crackers.

title: casserole sauce or soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. To use as a substitute for one can condensed soup, mix 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cups water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Makes 3 cups mix (equivalent to about 9 cans soup)

title: sally lunn
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and lard.
Beat in eggs and salt.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the flour; beat for 3 minutes on high speed of electric mixer.
Stir in milk and the softened yeast; mix well.
Add the remaining flour.
Beat 1 minute on high speed.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Grease in 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Stir down batter and spoon evenly into prepared pan. Cover and let rise again until double (30 to 45 minutes).

title: buttery caramel crisps
directions: Place graham cracker rectangles side by side in an ungreased jelly roll pan to cover bottom.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top. Combine butter, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla in saucepan.
Melt over medium heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Sprinkle coconut and almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: seafoam
directions: Make Jell-O as on package; let cool for about 15 minutes.
Mix in cream cheese with mixer.
Add pineapple and chill until firm. Last, fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Heat to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: traders punch
directions: Mix fruit juices and grenadine.
Pour over block of ice to chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale and berries or fruit. Makes 4 quarts.

title: aunt una's banana bread
directions: Blend butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add bananas.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon raisin bread pudding
directions: Peel and cube the apples.
In a saute pan, melt the butter, then add the apple cubes and brown sugar and saute until soft. Remove from heat.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Cut green pepper and onion and put in carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Set and marinate overnight.

title: sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Mix beef, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt and pepper. Form into 18 meat balls. Brown. Combine in same pan the juice, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar. Cook until thickened. Add meatballs, pineapple and peppers. Heat thoroughly; serve hot.

title: tastes like twice baked potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to directions on box.
Add cream cheese and eggs.
Beat well.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Halfway through, add onion rings.
Can be made ahead.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes in salted water until done, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Peel while hot and return to pan.
Add butter and the orange juice.
Mash until smooth.
Add pecans.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Cover with marshmallows and place in 400° oven until marshmallows start to melt and are lightly browned.
Watch carefully, marshmallows burn easily.
This is a traditional Thanksgiving dish in the South.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Roll the meat into small meatballs (seasoning optional).
Core cabbage and slice into 1-inch slices.
Put all ingredients into large pot and cover.
Cook on high flame for 1/2 hour.
Lower heat and keep covered for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
If you like more juice, add 1 more bottle of ketchup and 1 more liter of ginger ale.
Serves 10.

title: bird's nest
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan. Press out a small circle in middle of bread using a small glass. Place bread in frying pan and crack egg into the middle of the circle. Cook
until bread is toasted and flip over. Cook egg until desired taste. Place on a plate and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: lemony cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Set aside.
In medium bowl with electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in Jell-O.
Fold toping into cheese mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Needs no cooking.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.
Serve topped with cherry pie filling.

title: my mama's enchiladas
directions: Grate cheese and chop onion.
Steam meat with a little bit of grease.
Remove excess fat.
Add spices.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add chili.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Fry corn tortillas in hot oil until soft.
Lay aside.
Fill tortillas with preferred amount of meat, cheese and onion.
Fold snugly and place in pan.
Do all tortillas until pan is filled.
Heat enchilada sauce and pour over enchiladas in pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over enchiladas until they are completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Boil chicken and debone. Then boil spaghetti noodles in chicken broth. Melt margarine and saute onion and bell pepper. When spaghetti is ready, drain off water and put in a bowl with Velveeta cheese. Melt over spaghetti. Add in all other ingredients and put in covered dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls for a crowd
directions: Add shortening, salt and sugar to the boiling water.
Stir to dissolve; cool.
Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Beat the eggs and add to the cooled mixture.
Add the yeast and enough flour to make a dough.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down; roll and cut into biscuits.
Bake in a 375° oven.
Makes 50 biscuits.
Can be kept in the refrigerator for 3 days (keep punched down).

title: fruit and yogurt pie
directions: *I have used frozen strawberries.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Put rice and bouillon cubes in large pan; add water. Place chicken on top of rice in the water. Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°. Remove cover and let chicken brown during the last few minutes.

title: nippy corned beef "n" cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley, in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Shape into balls.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate until ready to use.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Roll in parsley until completely coated. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening, salt and vanilla; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one is added.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake 1/2 hour or more. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or two 9 x 9-inch pans.

title: nippy  cheese broccoli(microwave)
directions: Place butter in measuring cup and melt.
Blend in flour, salt and milk.
Microwave on High for 1 or 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Place broccoli on serving platter.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 6 or 8 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Drain well.
Top with cheese sauce and garnish with tomato slices.
Microwave on High for 2 or 3 minutes until hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch container.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Add cracker crumbs and brown.

title: frozen cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water and pour over butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour and other dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Form into rolls wrapped in waxed paper.
Chill in freezer until firm. Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice and bake for 10 minutes.

title: quickie casserole
directions: In bottom of 2-quart casserole, put in ground beef which has been lightly salted. Mix vegetables with soup and add on top of beef. Top with frozen Tater Tots. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's devil's cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Combine cocoa, 1/3 cup sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Beat eggs into sugar and shortening mix.
Pour cocoa mix into preceding and mix well.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate boneless chicken for 8 to 24 hours in equal parts soy sauce, lime juice and oil (enough to cover).
Broil meat until barely cooked.
While meat is broiling, saute vegetables in marinade until they are barely tender.
Slice meat and add to vegetables to simmer a few minutes.
Serve with tortillas.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; fry on buttered griddle.
Drain on brown paper in oven.
Makes 2 servings.

title: delicious lettuce salad
directions: Put lettuce, tomato, cucumber, grapes and raisins in bowl. Cook bacon and crumble.
Fry chicken breast in lemon pepper.
Add to salad and top with cheese.
Top with favorite dressing.

title: smothered steak
directions: Pound steak; add salt and pepper to flour.
Lightly coat steak and brown both sides.
Saute onion and celery.
Add other ingredients and meat.
Cover pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: orange and spice tea
directions: To convert recipes, substitute for each cup of white flour:

title: low sugar black cherry mold
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Whip until smooth. Heat cherries, pineapple juice and Jell-O.
Total liquid of juice and Coke should equal 3 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Blend in cream cheese.
Spray mold with Pam.
Pour into mold and freeze.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper until meat is done; drain fat.
Mix corn meal and salt.
Add flour, soda, milk, eggs and peppers.
Pour half of the corn meal mixture in pan.
Layer with corn, meat mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining corn meal mixture over top and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook until tender.
Add a can of green beans.

title: hula chill
directions: Mix juices. Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 10 small servings.

title: quesadillas
directions: Slice the cheese about 1/2 inch thick and place pieces to cover tortilla.
Top with another tortilla.
Put a thin coat of vegetable oil in a non-stick saute pan and heat until very hot. Place the filled tortilla in pan and grill, turning once until cheese is melted and tortilla is slightly browned.

title: st. george island jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage or pork.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients to browned meat.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add enough chicken stock to cover all of the ingredients fully.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: bacon-sausage-cheese omelet
directions: Note:
Need 10-inch frying pan and small bowl.

title: tamale squares
directions: Prepare cornmeal mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
