Mix cooked ground beef with Cheez Whiz, tomatoes and package of seasoning.
Pour hamburger mixture onto uncooked cornbread.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until done.

title: deep dish turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Over medium heat, gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuit mix; mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits.
Roll out to cover dish.
Cut slashes in center of dough.
Place on top of dish; crimp edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 4 tablespoons juice.
Mix salmon, eggs and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice and stir into salmon mixture.
Roll into patties and roll each in cracker crumbs or flour and fry in Crisco until brown.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine eggs, sauce, salt and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into hot oil.
Serves 6.

title: louisiana chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and soda together.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add unbeaten eggs to creamed mixture, then add dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk.
Add boiling water, then vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry-honey butter
directions: With electric mixer or food processor, whip butter and honey until soft and light on high speed.
Gradually beat in strawberries, blending smooth.
Pack in crocks.
Cover.
May be refrigerated up to 1 month.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together until crumbly the margarine, 2 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup sugar. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown on edges. Gradually add sugar, 1 1/2 cups, to beaten eggs; beat well. Blend in 1/3 cup flour, baking powder, lemon juice and salt. Pour over baked crust. Bake for 18 minutes more or until set. Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken robert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with dried beef.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each breast half.
Place on dried beef.
Dust with garlic powder.
Mix together the mushroom soup, sour cream and canned mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Dust with paprika.
Bake in the oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover if it gets too brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, use fork to slightly beat egg.
Add onion. If desired, stir in chili powder, then stir in salt and pepper. Add meat.
Mix together.
In large skillet, cook meat over high heat until beef is brown, then drain off fat.
While meat is cooking, drain beans, then stir beans and taco sauce into the cooked meat.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
While mixture is simmering, cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Place salad greens on large salad plates. Spoon warm meat mixture on top of greens.
Sprinkle cheese. Arrange tomatoes and chips around outer edges of plate.
If desired, serve with avocado dip, sour cream or salsa.
Makes 2 servings.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and sprinkle with the canning salt. Thinly slice the peppers and onion.
Add and mix well.
Add sugar, vinegar and celery seed. Let stand at room temperature until sugar is dissolved. Pack in freezer containers and freeze. Keeps indefinitely and can be refrozen.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Place by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Press with fork (like in peanut butter cookies).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.

title: hormel dip
directions: Heat chili in crock-pot or fondue pot.
Cut up cream cheese in bite size pieces; add to the dip.
Add 1 1/2 cups grated cheese; stir.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Serve with corn chips or tortillas.
Keep warm.

title: deluxe apple dumplings
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Make syrup of 2 cups sugar, 2 cups water and cinnamon.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and add butter.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Cut in shortening and add milk all at once.
Stir until moistened.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: In large bowl, grate with cheese grater the German chocolate bar. To

this, add all ingredients but the mini chocolate chips. With mixer, beat for 3 to 5 minutes. Add the mini chips and beat 1 more minute. When well mixed, pour into greased Bundt mold and bake about 1 hour at 350° or until tests done.

title: macaroni meat supper
directions: Brown meat with onion and salt; drain.
Stir in corn, stewed tomatoes and ketchup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni. Simmer 5 minutes more.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces of the almond bark in bowl on High for 2 minutes; stir additionally until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining 2 ounces bark and oil in glass measuring cup for 1 minute.
Continue until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut. Refrigerate until firm.
Store at room temperature.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Use strips of zucchini, squash, cauliflower or celery to dip.

title: noel christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in egg and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill one hour or overnight when blended into dough.
Roll out on floured shelf.
Cut out desired shapes.
Transfer to cookie sheets and brush with beaten egg white.
Decorate with sprinkles, etc.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Add flour and cook until flour is deep red brown.
Stir constantly to prevent burning.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in beef, pork, giblets, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is browned.
Blend in broth.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in rice and green onions.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gauteaux francais(french cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, milk and baking powder in a baking dish.
Spread batter evenly in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter in a bowl and add brown sugar and water.
Pour over batter mixture in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: breast chicken with stuffing
directions: Layer chicken breasts in Pyrex pan.
Place a slice of cheese on each breast half.
Add soup; cover with stuffing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana trifle
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Layer with vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas.
Top with whipped cream.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, corn syrups, butter and vanilla. Add chopped nuts and pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves over filling.
Bake at 375 for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325 degrees and bake 45 minutes more.

title: no bake cherry balls
directions: In mixing bowl, blend sugar, butter, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in coconut and chill for 1 hour.
Drain cherries on paper towel.
After mixture has chilled, shape about 1 tablespoon around cherry.
Leave stem showing.
Dip in graham cracker crumbs about 2/3 from bottom.
Refrigerate until served.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: veal stew
directions: Wash and peel onions.
Cut veal stew into pieces.
Combine veal and onions in a casserole dish.
Add salt, bay leaves, pepper, olive oil, peeled and chopped tomatoes, garlic and enough water to cover.
Cook, covered.
Stew for about one hour over low heat.

title: italian vegetable soup(tops recipe)
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add all ingredients except cabbage, beans and macaroni.
Bring to boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Toss with apples and lemon juice. Pour in pie shell.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust. Seal and flute edges.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 minutes.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo for a few minutes.
Mix with other ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Will make two casseroles, one can be frozen and baked later.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In separate bowl, mix mushroom soup with 1/4 cup milk.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Pour soup/milk mixture over top of loaf.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: choco-cherry cookies
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and cherries.

title: classic buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk and chicken pieces in a large bowl, coating each piece. Stir together flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika on a piece of wax paper. Working with one piece of chicken at a time, lift out of buttermilk and let drain over bowl. Gently shake off excess buttermilk, roll chicken in flour mixture to coat evenly, and place on a clean piece of wax paper.

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Combine egg whites and nuts; stir well.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Add sugar and cinnamon mixture to nuts, stirring well until coated.
Spread evenly on greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes; stir after 15 minutes.
Cool; remove from pan.
Store in airtight container.

title: pasta primavera with cheese sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook garlic until browned; remove garlic.
Add broccoli and red pepper to oil; stir until coated with oil.
Add 1/4 cup water; reduce heat to medium.
Cook until tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese spread, milk, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Cook until cheese melts and everything is blended.
Drain pasta.
Pour cheese and broccoli mixture over pasta.
Serve immediately.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and allow to boil gently for 8 minutes.

title: mozzarella cheese tarts
directions: Using biscuit cutter, cut out the center of each slice of bread.
Press center of bread gently with fingertips to form an indention.
Fill with 1 level tablespoon of grated cheese.
Fold in half.
Use a fork to press edges and seal.
Brush tarts with melted butter.
Sprinkle garlic salt on top.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Turn over and bake 5 minutes more.
Dip in pizza sauce to use as appetizers.

title: milk chocolate bubble ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Melt butter or margarine.
Separate biscuits.
Flatten each biscuit into a 3-inch circle.
Place a kiss in the center of each biscuit.
Wrap biscuit around chocolate forming a ball. Repeat with remaining chocolate and biscuits.

title: devil-dog cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonful on a cookie sheet.
Leave ample space between.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: andrea's beef casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef until crumbly.
Saute onion and pepper then add to ground beef.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes to ground beef mixture.
Season with garlic salt and simmer.
Pour hamburger mixture into a buttered 9x13-inch casserole dish.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potatoes.
Mix and add to package of hash browns.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: goulash
directions: Combine beef, sausage and onion; fry until meat is done and onion is tender.
Drain if necessary.
Cook noodles in water according to directions; drain and salt and pepper to taste. Combine meat mixture, mushrooms and soup with noodles, heating through before serving.

title: apple fritters
directions: Prepare pancake batter.
Slice bananas.
Dip in pancake batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: microwave chinese chicken with rice
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce.
Brush chicken with sauce; reserve remaining portion.
In large, shallow microwave dish, place chicken on wooden trivet, breast side down.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on Medium setting for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from microwave and turn chicken breast side up.
Brush generously with soy-margarine sauce.
Cover with wax paper and continue to microwave on Medium setting for 15 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease and leg moves freely when lifted or twisted.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter; add beef and cook.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: carameled popcorn
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil except soda.
Boil until hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add soda and stir until it gets foamy.
Pour over popcorn.
Add peanuts.

title: oven baked stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces or cubes.
Combine mushroom soup with water and dry onion mix.
Place meat and soup mixture in deep casserole and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Can also add 2 to 3 tablespoons sour cream before serving.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Line a baking sheet with waxed paper; set aside.
Pour sugar in small bowl and set aside.
In another small bowl, combine cream cheese, extract and food coloring.
Stir with wooden spoon. Gradually add powdered sugar and stir until well blended.
Mixture will become quite stiff and may require kneading as one would for dough.
When well mixed, form into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on baking sheet and press flat with the tines of a fork.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cranberry nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, sugars and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in cranberries and nuts. Drop by spoon fulls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for two minutes before removing to wire rack.
Makes about five dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter honey balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Roll in coconut or nuts.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Pare zucchini, remove pulp and seeds.
Chop zucchini, pepper and onion and set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling. Add all of the vegetables and cook for 5 minutes.
Can by your favorite method.
Great on hot dogs!

title: cheese ball
directions: With hands, blend all ingredients except nuts, until thoroughly combined.
Roll into ball or log.
Roll in the nuts. Makes 1 cheese ball about 6-inches in diameter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan. Bake in preheated moderate 350° oven about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: banana bread
directions: *For Sour Milk:
Mix 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar and milk to make 1 cup.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Butter	and
flour a 10-inch tube pan.	Thoroughly cream together
sugar
and butter.
Add eggs 1 at a time beating well after
each addition.
Mix in half the flour, then the whipping cream, then the other half of the flour.
Add vanilla or lemon. Pour
batter into prepared pan.
Set in cold oven and turn heat to 350°.
Bake
to
minutes.	Cool
in
pan 5 minutes. Elvis' favorite.

title: shrimp dress a chicken
directions: Lightly season chicken breasts with salt, pepper and sage. Slice onion and place in small casserole dish.
Place breasts in the dish with the onion slices.
Add cornmeal and blend meal with chicken breasts and onion.
Place small shrimp over breaded breasts.
Add milk.
Bake in oven at 370° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk, cool to lukewarm.
In small bowl dissolve yeast and 3 teaspoons sugar with 1/2 cup water.
In large bowl add milk, sugar, salt, shortening, water and yeast.
Then add flour and mix well.
Place on floured pastry board and knead.
Place into greased container until double in size.
Divide dough in 2 parts.
Press or roll to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Shape round balls and place onto well-greased pans.
Cover with cloth when double in size.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple-nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine egg, milk, shortening, undrained pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Add dry ingredients all at once, stirring, just until moistened.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread mixture in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: stuffed baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
At stem end, pare skin 1/3 of the way down.
Stuff apples with figs and walnuts and place in a shallow dish.
In small pan, combine cinnamon candies, sugar and water. Boil 10 minutes; pour over apples.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, basting often with syrup until apples are tender. Pour off syrup to saucepan and boil until slightly thickened.
Pour over apples.
Serve warm or chilled, plain or with cream.

title: shortcut italian cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg yolks, oleo, buttermilk and vanilla with electric mixer.
Fold in coconut, pecans and 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in following order:

spinach (sprinkled with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar), bacon, eggs, lettuce (sprinkled with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar), peas, onion, mayonnaise (spread over top), Swiss and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate, toss and serve next day.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Crumble brownies and place in large container.
Sprinkle coffee over brownies.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Crush candy cars.
Add candy to pudding (reserving 1/4 c.).
Add 4 cups cool whip to pudding, add cream cheese, sugar and nuts, blend together.
Pour pudding mixture over brownies.
Top with remaining cool whip.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. butterfingers on top.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Pour ingredients in pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch a la mode
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix oats, flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place half the mixture in pan.
Cover with cranberry sauce; top with rest of mixture. Bake 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cut in squares and top with ice cream.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Chop in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Be sure to stir well.
Keep covered in refrigerator at least 1 hour (better over night) before using.
Flour hands and pinch off enough dough to roll into shape of a biscuit, place on greased pan and let rise 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 - 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat.
In Dutch oven, brown meat in Crisco.
Add soup, water, basil, onion and celery. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Pare and cube the potatoes and carrots into 1-inch pieces.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 375° or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, refrigerate 1 hour or longer. Serve with chips-makes 4 1/2 cups of dip.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Cream margarine with brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts; mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Blend sugar with softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well. Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, bell pepper and sugar; toss lightly. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over shredded cabbage mixture and toss lightly.
Cover; chill at least 4 hours.
Salad keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: french bean pot
directions: Brown sausage, onion and minced garlic in olive oil.
Mix all ingredients in slow cooker or crock-pot.
Cook on slow 7 to 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Nothing in recipe needs to be exact.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil breasts until tender; boil potatoes until tender and chop chicken.
Place in pie shell.
Put layer of potatoes, then layer of peas and carrots.
In skillet, melt butter; add flour, then broth to make a gravy.
Pour over pie.
Add other pie crust on top.
Pinch together to seal.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: chocolate chip brown sugar cookies
directions: Measure and sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips and nuts; blend well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix together; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Combine softened cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and juice, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Pour mixture over crust.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Combine sour cream, vanilla and sugar. Spread carefully over cheese cake.
Continue baking for 10 minutes. Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool before removing rims of pan. Chill.

title: ham, cheese and sausage souffle
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread half bread cubes evenly in dish.
Add ham, sausage and cheeses.
Add rest of bread.
Mix eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour evenly over souffle.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: cherry soup
directions: Cook about 1/2 to 1 quart of cherries in 3 quarts of water with about 1/4 cup of sugar.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Grease large oblong baking dish.
Put light coating of cracker crumbs in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle onion and broken pieces of cheese slices over onoins.
Add can of water to soup and bring to a boil in saucepan.
Add the tuna, pimentos, bell pepper, peas, evaporated milk and pepper.
Mix and pour over crackers, onion and cheese.
Sprinkle a few cracker crumbs over the top.
Put more cheese over that.
Dot with margarine and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until it's bubbly and a little brown.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan.
Add cornmeal, all at once. Beat vigorously with wire whisk until smooth.
Raise heat, stirring constantly.

Boil for 1 minute, then put heat to low and cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent scorching. Remove from heat, stir in butter until melted, then stir in molasses, sugar, nutmeg, salt and ginger.
Stir in eggs and raisins.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Set baking dish in a large pan filled with 1-inch of water.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: caramels
directions: Combine in
heavy pot with wooden spoon.
Cook over low heat until 250° on candy thermometer.
Take off stove and stir in 2 teaspoons
vanilla.
Pour in greased pan, 9 x 13-inches. Cool and cut into pieces; wrap in waxed paper.
Hard to cut if too cold.

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Combine in order given and pour into jar.
Shake well and refrigerate.

title: beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine, cocoa and butter.
Add eggs, and vanilla, mix well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Continue to beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into sheet cake pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread marshmallow cream over cake while hot.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Grease microwave ring mold and coat with crumbs.
Mix all dry ingredients; make well in center.
Add rest of ingredients after mixing them together.
Spoon into mold and microwave on Medium 8 minutes.
Rotate after 4 minutes and bake 1 1/2 minutes longer or until cake pulls away from sides of mold.
Let stand 10 minutes; invert onto plate.
Glaze with lemon juice and powdered sugar mixture.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Add sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip. Mix well.
Layer in a large bowl the vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas. Repeat until all pudding is used.
Seal with the other half of the Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick (medium heat). Remove from heat; add red food coloring (few drops) and jello. Mix well and cool to lukewarm.
Place whole, washed and dried berries in pie crust.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Melt margarine and add to it the brown sugar, flour and nuts. Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into one loaf or several small ones.
Bake at 400° about 1 hour.
If small ones, about 45 minutes.

title: gluten steaks bake
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes, reserving mushroom liquid.
Remove onions and mushrooms from pan. Dip steaks in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs and saute in oil. Place alternate layers of steaks, onions and mushrooms in buttered casserole.
Mix liquid from steaks with mushroom liquid and sour cream; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except vinegar and beat until well blended.
Add vinegar and beat thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1-1/4 c.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: In a heavy sauce pan over low heat, melt margarine and chocolate chips. Remove from heat. Gently stir in rice cereal until completely coated. Press into bottom and sides of a 9 inch pie plate. Chill 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/3 cup mix in cup.
Add hot water.

title: lorraine's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: "budget" crab salad
directions: Add first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise to moisten.
Let set 1/2 hour before serving.
Tastes like the real thing.

title: cranberry surprise muffins
directions: Cut cream cheese into 12 equal cubes; set aside.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Ready to eat.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix up all ingredients, except whole milk.
Put into ice cream freezer can.
Fill can to line with whole milk.
Freeze according to instructions.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; add ground beef last.
Mix well. Press into 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°; uncover last 10 minutes.

title: black bean 'n rice salada
directions: Toss all ingredients. Chill and enjoy. Easy.

title: very good pinto beans
directions: Bring beans to a boil for 30 minutes.
Then put all ingredients in beans and cook until done, about 2 hours.

title: lemon dill rice(heart healthy)
directions: Combine the stock, wine, onion, bay leaf, lemon juice and zest and bring it to a boil. Add the rice to the boiling stock and stir once with a fork to separate the grains. Cover the pot and place it in a moderate oven (350°F/175°C) for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until the rice has absorbed all of the liquid. Remove the cover; fluff the rice with a fork and fold in the chopped dill. Re-cover and allow to rest 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Yield: 4 portions.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients; serve with apples.
May be made the day before.

title: orange marinated vegetables
directions: Drain vegetables, if necessary.
In a large bowl mix vegetables, olives and orange peel.
Pour in dressing; toss to coat.
Cover and chill to marinate at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving lightly drain.
Serve with cocktail picks.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients together in a jar and shake well.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 cup with 7 calories per 2 tablespoons.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Fry hamburger and drain well.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 20 to 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch; peel.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Boil slowly 5 minutes; cool.

title: veggie squares
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and onion soup together and spread on crescent rolls.
Mix 3/4 cup of vegetable combination of your choice, chopped fine with 3/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture and chill.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: honey syrup carrots
directions: In a saucepan, add carrots, butter and water.
Cook until tender.
Drain the liquid off into another saucepan and add honey to liquid.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour honey mixture over carrots and serve.

title: simmered hawaii
directions: Great recipe for leftover ham.

title: easy beef dinner
directions: Cook potatoes; mash.
Brown beef and onion.
Spread mashed potatoes on serving platter; spoon hamburger mixture on top of potatoes.
Spread ketchup on top.
Serve with green vegetables.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Place in baking dish.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients.
Spread over broccoli.
Cover with the additional cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deviled cheese dunk
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, chips or fresh vegetables.
May also be used as sandwich spread.

title: berta's mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first six ingredients together until lumps are gone.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a thick batter; will be thick and heavy.
Roll hot dogs in batter and fry at 375° until done.

title: bird of paradise punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two (9-inch) pans.
Mix ingredients, except frosting.
Mix on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost cake.

title: "frech" bread pizza
directions: Pop toast pieces in a toaster.
Take them out.
Put a piece of cheese in the middle and eat it!

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown 1 pound sausage; drain off fat.
In a mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients together.
Roll into balls or drop by the teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: ooie gooie cake
directions: Stir cake mix, 2 eggs and oleo together and spread in 11 x 17-inch ungreased pan and pat flat.
Blend powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese and spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter strips
directions: Trim crusts from bread. Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 200° or until dry; do not brown.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Start adding sugar gradually and beat until mixture stands in a soft peak.
Fold in vanilla, crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Spread evenly in well-greased pie plate and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a soft dough.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Cut into strips about 2-inches by 2-inches.
Drop into simmering chicken broth.
Cook until done (about 15 minutes).
Can be used with any stewed wild game.

title: quick roast turkey
directions: Prepare turkey for roasting.
Place on heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Seal securely to prevent drippings from escaping in pan. Place foil wrapped bird, breast up, in bottom of roaster.
Roast in very hot oven at 450°.
About 15 to 20 minutes before total roasting time, remove from oven.
Gently remove foil away from bird to edges of pan.
Continue to roast until brown.
Sometimes bird is already brown enough at this point.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart mixer bowl add confectioners sugar and softened butter.
Mix on low speed until combined.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat on high speed until fluffy (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Spread on cooled butter cookies.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first five ingredients to the soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add the marshmallow cream and peanut butter. Beat until firm.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan. Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best of the west beans
directions: Brown meats and onion; drain excess fat.
Mix separately the remaining ingredients except beans and simmer about 15 minutes. Pour meats and beans into simmered mixture and heat to boiling or, put in oven and bake at 350° until hot.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, cornstarch and water in double boiler and cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally. Just before removing from heat, stir in the two small lumps of butter and lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pico de gallo (salsa)
directions: Squeeze juice from limes into a nonaluminum bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and season with salt to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, celery soup and water in pan that you will bake it in.
Sprinkle Minute rice over soup mixture.
Add cup-up chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Cover with tin foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add broth and potatoes; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.

title: cozy apple brown betty
directions: Brown the bread crumbs in the butter.
Place 1/3 of the bread crumbs in the bottom of a baking dish and add half of the apples. Sprinkle this with lemon juice and brown sugar.
Then add 1/3 of the bread crumbs.
Top with the remaining apples, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Cover with the remainder of the bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve this with warm ice cream, milk or whipped cream.

title: pecan stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Mash yolks with fork. Add balance of ingredients.
Spoon mixture into whites.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley.
Sprinkle on grated pecans for garnish.

title: indian cabbage
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove bacon.
Add water, sugar, salt, cabbage and corn.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with crumbled bacon on top.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken in 4 cups water until tender.
Cool and remove bones, saving the broth.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Dice and fry bacon; remove from skillet and brown beef and onion in the pan. Add bacon, chicken broth, salt, paprika and tomatoes.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining vegetables and chicken and simmer for another 30 minutes.
Thicken with flour and add seasoning.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic and saute until tender.
Stir in hominy and remaining ingredients, except cheese. Spoon mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 items, then mix in the rest and blend well. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix crackers, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese. Pour over crust. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll and secure with a toothpick.
Chill several hours.
Slice 1/2 or 1-inch thick.

title: chicken la grande
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange chicken in pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
This makes a lot of sauce which can be served over rice.

title: wisconsin wurst
directions: Brown wurst on grill.
Cook onion, pepper and wurst in beer. Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: fruit on a stick
directions: Cut all fruit into bite size pieces.
Mix cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and milk until smooth.
Thread fruit on wooden skewers.
Serve with dip.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: german chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in a 13 x 9 inch pyrex dish.
Brown sausage, drain well.
Mash up sausage and spoon over bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over sausage/cheese mixture.
Let sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Drop in beef, a portion at a time; shake until coated.
Mix with oil in 3 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir once.
Add vegetables, water and tomato sauce; mix well.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1/3 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan with broccoli.
After butter is melted and frozen broccoli broken up, add rest of ingredients. Stir.
Place in casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: mint tea
directions: Put tea, sugar and mint (squeeze leaves slightly, but not the stem) into a 2-quart container.
Pour boiling water over and keep covered for 5 minutes.
Strain. Cool and then add lemon juice. Makes 2 quarts.

title: creamy holiday fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate over boiling water, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, stir in milk, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Spread mixture evenly into waxed paper lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board and peel off paper and cut into squares. Tightly cover any leftovers.
However, there are seldom any leftovers!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat peanut butter, water, butter, eggs and half of the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
Drop dough by teaspoon 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
With fork dipped in flour, flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix vegetables together; add salt and stir well.
Chill 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour into a large dish; cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: coffee mocha punch
directions: **Simple syrup (one cup water and one cup sugar boiled together).

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; cook and stir until mixture thickens.

Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Spoon over peppermint ice cream and enjoy!! Getting peppermint ice cream for the holidays and serving Sandy's chocolate sauce over it adds up to the best dessert ever!!
The potluck group (and most of our families) always serve this at Christmas!!

title: never fail corn pudding
directions: Cut corn off cob, scraping cob.
Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Blend in beaten eggs, butter and milk.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix everything, except cheese; put in greased casserole.
Heat until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt cheese, don't burn.

title: chef salad dressing
directions: Mix.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, then it's all ready.

title: alex's mini meat loaves(kid recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup and brown sugar.
Put in ungreased muffin tin.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mozzarella cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Great with Fritos.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half (long-ways).
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pudding, then top with Cool Whip.
Favorite for young children; adults, too!

title: debbie's brisket
directions: Place brisket in large baking dish. Cover with soup mix, chili sauce and beer. Cover tightly and bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours. Remove from oven; slice very thinly. Mix sauce together and return meat to pan. Cover with sauce; heat, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Serve.

title: herbed goat cheese
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except cheese, for 5 minutes. Cool. Arrange cheese slice on a serving platter. Pour mixture over cheese. Serve with small slices of French bread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sugars and cornstarch together; add water, margarine and vanilla.
Cook on medium heat until bubbly and thick; pour over sliced sweet potatoes, layering potatoes and syrup. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: virginia apple pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk to butter.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Pile apples in middle.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 18 (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin pan cups. Remove paper from peanut butter candies. Prepare brownie mix as label directs.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Place a candy on top of each cupcake. Bake 20 to 25 minutes (until toothpick inserted next to candy comes out clean).
Cool cupcakes in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from cups, loosening sides with knife, if necessary. Cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 18 cupcakes.
Each cake contains 275 calories.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix pears, sugar, flour, cinnamon, and salt; pour into one pie crust. Dot with oleo; cover pie filling with remaining, thawed pie shell. Seal edges and make slits in top. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure, add baking powder and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg, then flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: chicken and corn soup
directions: Wash noodles in cold water and add to the chicken stock.
Cook until soft, then add the chicken and corn.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the parsley and egg.
Serve hot with an inch square of French bread on each cup.
Chicken and corn soup is of German descent.

title: kathy's meat dish
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together.
Add beans, rice and cheese.
Heat thoroughly.

title: almond crackers
directions: Spray jellyroll pan (or cookie sheet) with Pam. Put 1 layer of Club House crackers (1 package) on cookie sheet or pan. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bring butter, oleo and sugar to a rolling boil and pour over the crackers covered with almonds. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan. Put onto another cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: ice box bran muffins
directions: Mix Nabisco Bran and boiling water together.
Set aside. Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk and Nabisco mixture and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add All-Bran.
Fold into the Nabisco Bran mixture.
Bake as many as you want at 425° for 17 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Will keep in refrigerator for about 1 month.
Make 4 1/2 quarts.

title: first-prize potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in salted water to cover in large saucepan. Bring to boil.
Cook just until tender when pierced with fork, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch chunks.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine first four ingredients and let stand 15 to 20 minutes. Beat well.

title: avocado salsa
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill. Just before serving, add avocado and toss gently.
Serve with chips, chicken or seafood.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter pie(serves 8)
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip and crust.
Fold Cool Whip in last.
Pour into chocolate Ready-Crust pie crust. Decorate with chocolate syrup or small chocolate chips.

title: georgianna's tortilla soup
directions: Put chicken in a 4 or 5-quart pot.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Skim off foam that rises to surface.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is very tender.
Remove from broth and refrigerate separately overnight.

title: sausage, bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and place in 2 1/2 gallon large heavy pot.
Add onion and garlic salt.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 additional hours, stirring occasionally.
The lower the temperature you can cook the beans and still simmer, the better.
Serves 12 to 15 folks.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt oleo and chocolate; cool slightly.
Blend in sugar and eggs (one at a time); beat for 1 minute.
Add walnuts and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Fit one refrigerated pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate according to package directions.
Combine chicken, vegetables, soup and pepper; spoon into pie crust.
Place remaining crust on top.
Fold edges under and flute.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon in dishes.
Garnish as desired.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and stir in corn.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine slaw, celery and onions.
Make dressing with vinegar, sugar, oil, pepper and flavor packet from soup.
Mix well.
Add to vegetable mix and toss.
Crumble Ramen noodles and toss with vegetables.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix.
Drop very small portions on greased cookie sheet. Flatten very thin with fork.
Cook in 350° oven for 10 minutes (not very brown).

title: hanky panky(appetizer)
directions: Brown meats together; pour off most of the fat.
Break the cheese into small pieces; stir into hot meat.
Put 1 teaspoon of all ingredients on each slice of bread; spread.
To serve immediately, put on cookie sheet and brown in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zesty spinach salad
directions: In a small bowl or jar with a tight fitting lid, combine the first 7 ingredients. Mix well.
Chill.
Just before serving, lightly toss spinach, radishes, eggs, onion and bacon in a large salad bowl. Mix the dressing again.
Pour over salad and toss. Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie mixture on greased pizza pan (spread out). Cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over cooled cookie.
Put on sliced fruit.
Glaze.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Then add soda, flour and oats.
Spread on a large cookie sheet (13 x 18 x 1-inch), lightly greased.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool and frost with peanut butter and/or chocolate frosting.
Serves 30.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss until well mixed.
Top with pepperoni.

title: beef tips
directions: Line square baking pan with aluminum foil.
Put 1 tablespoon margarine in bottom of pan.
Mix onion soup mix, water and steak sauce together.
Put half of the mixture in the pan.
Add beef chunks.
Put the other half of the mixture on top of beef. Sprinkle mushrooms on top.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Fold foil over top to seal in juices.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat egg, milk, baking powder and salt together.
Add the flour to make a thick waffle batter.
Turn mixture out onto a floured board.
Knead in flour until stiff enough to roll out. Cut into skinny slices.
Put into your hot liquid; cook about 2 minutes.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix everything together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. It will not look like there
is enough liquid, but the next morning there will be plenty.

title: stir-fry sauce mix
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons corn oil over medium heat.
Add the carrots, green peppers and onions; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove vegetables from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon corn oil and the chicken strips; stir-fry for 2 minutes, or until chicken turns white.
Return vegetables, Stir in the Stir-Fry Sauce Mix. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.

title: wine muffins(serves 12)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on muffins.
Broil for 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Cut into eighths.

title: irish griddle soda farl
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into a bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in buttermilk.
Mix to a rough dough with a fork. Turn out onto lightly floured working surface.
Knead lightly. Pat out to a circle and using a floured knife, cut into pie shaped wedges, about 8.
Preheat griddle or heavy skillet.
Place dough on it and bake slowly for about 5 minutes on each side. Serve with butter.

title: easy zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Slice zucchini.
Put in pot with 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Cook for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cupcake ice cream cones
directions: Mix cake according to its directions.
Fill cones about 1/2 full of cake batter.
Set cones in muffin pan.
Bake about 20 minutes or until top springs back.
Batter will rise giving appearance of an ice cream cone.
Frost as desired adding decoration according to occasion, such as jelly beans for Easter or Halloween or dye some coconut green for Easter.
Easy to make. Fun to decorate.

title: mom's light biscuits(19th century - mary lillian evelyn rainier thomas, 1870-1945)
directions: I make this as it calls for.
In a large bowl mix lard, sugar, salt and warm water.
Add to this the yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough and knead well.
Keep in cool place.
Pinch off when needed.
Let raise until double in size.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Place bread on top of sausage and cheese.
Mix all the other stuff and pour over.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: light rolls
directions: Warm milk and water.
Put in a bowl; then stir in yeast.
Let set until yeast is dissolved.
Stir in salt, sugar, egg, Crisco and 2 cups flour.
Let rise a few minutes; then knead in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Let dough rise until light; then make into small rolls in a 9 x 12-inch pan; let rise again until light.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberries smetana
directions: Combine strawberries with both liqueurs.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar or more to taste.
Let strawberries and liqueurs marinate for 3 or 4 hours in refrigerator.
Spoon strawberries onto serving dishes.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle heavily with brown sugar.

title: pigs in a yoke
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, heat milk, butter and salt just until butter melts.
Blend in flour quickly.
Do not handle dough too much.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Fit into 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Flute edge. Pour filling into dough lined pan.
Arrange sausages in rows on filling.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until golden.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 400°.
Brown meat in frypan and remove. Heat 1 cup cooking oil.
To soften tortillas, dip in hot oil and drain.
Set aside on plate.
In another plate, pour some enchilada sauce and dip tortillas in sauce.
Fill each tortilla with 1 tablespoon of meat and 1 teaspoon cheese.
Roll up and put in oblong baking dish with seams down.
Continue until all tortillas are filled.
Heat enchilada sauce with mushroom soup until warm. Pour over filled tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese and sliced olives over top and bake in preheated oven until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.

title: tarragon marinated shrimp
directions: Remove tails from shrimp.
Combine shrimp, oils, vinegar, peppercorn, parsley, tarragon, onion and lemon slices in large bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours, tossing frequently.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and make balls.
Place in baking dish. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: marbled cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons margarine over low heat in double boiler, stirring constantly.
In first bowl, put 2 tablespoons margarine and cream cheese; cream until softened. Gradually add sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in egg, flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until blended.
In second bowl, beat 2 eggs until fluffy and light in color; gradually add 3/4 cup of sugar and beat until thickened.
Fold in baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in the cool mixture.
Stir in vanilla, almond extract and nuts.
Measure 1 cup of chocolate batter and set aside.

title: old-fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Add milk and cream, reserving some of the liquid to mix with flour.
Mix flour with reserved milk to form a smooth paste.
Add to the custard mixture along with the salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook until mixture begins to thicken and coats the spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Allow to cool.
Then pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
In a mixing bowl, mix onion, soup and shredded cheese. Add broccoli and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Remove outer layers.
Cut off top and bottom.
Simmer in water, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove center to make onion shells.

title: fragrant chili
directions: Brown beef, adding onion, celery and carrot.
After beef is browned through, add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
(No need to add salt; canned ingredients have more than enough!) Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
This tasty chili will satisfy even the hungriest bears in your den!

title: lazy day pie
directions: Heat peaches until hot.
Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish.
Mix together the sugar, flour and water.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Pour hot peaches on top.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until crust is done.

title: stuffed cabbages by louis carter
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water and set aside.
Brown ground meat and onions.
Add rice, sweet pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for a few minutes.

Place a small amount of mixture in middle of wilted cabbage leaves and roll up to form a ball. Place the formed cabbage leaves in bottom of large pot and pour tomatoes over the cabbages and cook over medium heat for approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all the filling ingredients and pile into graham cracker crusts.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, applesauce, cocoa, butter, water, eggs, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat on low speed scraping bowl occasionally for 3 minutes.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done. Remove from pan and cool.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Mix all vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Tie mixed spices in a bag. Add sugar and other spices to vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients until hot and well seasoned.
Remove spice bag. Hot pack into hot jars and seal.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Peel carrots and grate.
Combine with drained pineapple, raisins, orange juice and yogurt.
Serves 6.

title: herbs and cheese bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Cut bread in half lengthwise and place on a baking sheet.
Spread mayonnaise mixture or cut side of each bread half; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into slices and serve immediately.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground chuck and drain off fat.
Mix in remaining ingredients and bake in 350° to 400° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garlic toast
directions: Melt butter in hot skillet.

Add garlic powder and stir. Fry bread in garlic butter. Leave whole or cut into squares. Multiply recipe as desired. Very good, but uses quite a bit of butter. May need to add butter to "fry" second side.

title: smoked sausage
directions: Number 1:
Spread thick sliced Spam with a paste of brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Bake 15 minutes in hot oven.

title: navajo bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in lard.
Knead in enough water to make soft dough.
Form into flat disks, pricking several small holes with fork or fingers to prevent bubbling of bread. Fry in deep fryer to desired golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 (6-inch) disks.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail.
Mix other ingredients and chill.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight can.
Shake before using.
Use 2 rounded teaspoons per cup.
Add boiling water.

title: cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Cut 1 roll into 5 pieces about 1/2-inch wide.
Hollow out almost all the way to edge.
Mix together rest of ingredients and stuff rolls.
Bake at about 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Different and delicious!)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan with Crisco and then a light coating of flour. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add soda to flour.
Add eggs, bananas, flour and nuts to shortening mixture.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 1 hour).
If it browns too fast, turn heat down.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Place raw hamburger in bottom of small roaster or casserole dish.
Add sliced onion, salt and pepper.
Cover with a layer of corn, then spread Tater Tots on top.
Spread soups on Tater Tots and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and Wesson oil in microwave enough to dissolve. Pour over remaining ingredients and chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch for children
directions: Combine defrosted fruit juices.
Add cherry juice and chilled ginger ale.
Stir well.
Pour over fruit ice ring into punch bowl.
Garnish each punch cup with orange slice and cherry.
This is a very attractive punch for the children during the holidays.

title: cindy's easy cream soup
directions: Mix powdered milk and flour; cut in margarine (store in covered container in fridge).
Now you can add this mixture to water.
Make it creamy to your desire; then add anything from list.

title: stuffed eggs with crabmeat
directions: Hard-cook eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with fork.
Take out any cartilage from crabmeat that may be present.
Combine crabmeat, yolks, celery, dry mustard, salt and pepper with mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stuff egg whites and garnish, first with paprika and then a small amount of parsley.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°f. 150°c. gas mark 2. Set aside 1 cup of dry cake mix. In a large bowl combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and the oil, the mixture will be crumbly. Press crust mixture evenly into the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. In the same bowl, blend the cream cheese and sugar. Add the remaining 3 eggs and the reserved cake mix. Beat for 1 minute at medium speed. At low speed, add the milk, vanilla and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into the pie crust and bake for 45-55 minutes until the center is firm. Allow to cool then top with the pie filling. Chill before serving.

title: "candy bar" cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add powdered sugar and cream well. Add vanilla, milk and salt.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
If necessary, chill for easier handling.
Roll out dough, half at a time on surface sprinkled with powdered sugar to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Trim sides with fluted pizza cutter.
Cut in 3 x 1 1/2-inch rectangles and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 16 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool.
Spread 1 teaspoon filling on each.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon icing.
Decorate with pecan half, if desired.

title: holiday spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave the sugar, Karo, raw peanuts and oleo for 10 minutes, stirring once.
Add vanilla and soda. Stir until foamy. Quickly spread very thin on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool, then break in pieces.

title: congo bars
directions: Bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ripe tomato jam
directions: Scald, peel and quarter tomatoes.
Place in a preserving kettle.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Put spices in a muslin bag.
Simmer stirring frequently, until thick.

title: cheesy italian mini pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Unroll dough. Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut each half crosswise into thirds. Place 3 pieces pizza crust dough on greased cookie sheets.
Press each into 5-inch square.
Top each with 1/6 of bacon, pepperoni, sauce, onions and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown around edges.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamed.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes (may not appear to be done).
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix margarine, shortening, water and cocoa in a pan; let come to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Beat buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: best lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, beating
well
after each addition.
Add milk and sifted (flour, baking
powder
and
salt) alternately.
Add lemon and almond extracts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and twenty minutes or until cake
test	proves	done.
Let cool 5 minutes in greased tube pan before turning out.

title: cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grate cheese; set aside.
Combine beef, eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, salt, oregano and pepper.
Saute onions in a little vegetable oil until golden brown; add to meat mixture and mix well.
Turn out on sheet of aluminum foil and flatten into an oblong, about 1-inch thick.
Place ham slices on oblong, keeping them about 1-inch from edge.
Sprinkle grated cheese on ham.
Use the foil to fold meat mixture over ham and cheese, closing all openings.
Turn loaf from foil into a greased loaf pan.
Pat with fingers to fill in corners of pan and shape loaf, which will completely fill pan and be rounded slightly on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours, depending on degree of doneness desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute in skillet the oleo, onion and bell pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix together with sauteed ingredients.
Top with Velveeta cheese or Monterey Jack cheese. Top with bacon bits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter until smooth. Add Rice Krispies and form into balls. Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice, salt and water into a heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until rice is tender (15 or 20 minutes). Stir in milk and raisins.
Add beaten eggs into rice mixture. Return to low heat.
Cook while stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nutmeg. Serve hot or cold.

title: salmon cakes with couscous
directions: Drain the salmon and combine with egg, bread crumbs, lemon juice, cumin and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Shape into 4 patties.
Dice onion and red peppers.
In a saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add stock and bring to a boil.
Stir in the couscous, red peppers, raisins, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: almond dunking cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in sour cream and almond.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in almonds.
Divide dough into thirds.
Shape each portion into a 10-inch log.
Flatten log to 1/2 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Cut diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Put cut side down on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: spinach casserole - microwave
directions: Cook spinach, covered for 5-6 minutes or until steaming.
Cut butter and cheese into course pieces.
Add eggs, flour, and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add spinach and mix.
Butter 1/2 qt. casserole dish and put mixture in.
Cook 12-14 minutes at full power.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: shrimp and crab ball
directions: Reserve choice pieces
of crab "leg" meat for garnish.
In a large mixing bowl, mix 1/2 of the cocktail sauce and all other ingredients until blended.
Shape mixture into a log and spread with remaining cocktail sauce. Garnish top of log with crab legs and the perimeter of the log with lemon slices.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Combine the beaten eggs, milk and melted fat. Add gradually to dry ingredients, stirring only until batter is smooth. Add fruit pulp and drop by spoonfuls into oil heated 365° to 370°. Remove when light brown on both sides (need to flip) about 2 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: miss polly's irish potato candy
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until potatoes can be easily pierced with a fork.
Drain and let cool completely at room temperature.
Once cool, mix enough powdered sugar to give consistency of dough.
On dough board, dusted with powdered sugar; roll potatoes out flat.
Cover top of potatoes with peanut butter. Roll dough from side to side forming a long, round loaf.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until chilled.
Cut into 1-inch thick slices and serve.
This is great for kids to try!

title: onion popovers
directions: Combine all the ingredients until smooth.
Fill well oiled muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 to 15 more minutes.
Cool slightly, then take out of pan.
Yummie.

title: raisin cake
directions: Stew raisins 20 minutes in 2 cups of water.
Use both milk and raisin juice to make thin batter.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Toss lightly, except chow mein noodles.
Sprinkle 1 cup chow mein noodles over the top.
Bake at 375° for about 15 or 20 minutes, or until heated through.

title: orange prune bread
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling orange juice over prunes; let stand for 15 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs and stir well.
Add prune mixture, flour, salt and soda; mix well, then add the nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add this to creamed mixture.
Blend 2 teaspoons vanilla into applesauce and add soda.
Blend with batter using a wooden spoon.
Batter will be stiff so stir until well mixed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle warm tops with sugar, if desired.
Batter will keep in refrigerator a few days.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into a pizza pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: gummies pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and mix flour with it.
Mix everything (except vanilla and pecans) together.
When you get it all mixed up, add vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use iron skillet on low to medium-low heat. Cook until thick and smooth.
Pour hot pudding mixture over bananas and wafers. Use egg whites for topping.
In mixing bowl, mix 3 egg whites with 1 tablespoon sugar. Stir until thick.
Spoon it on top of the pudding.
Place in oven on broil until light brown on top.

title: punch supreme
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.
To make this an alcoholic punch, decrease the Sprite to 2 cans and add 1/2 pint of vodka.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetables.
Great dip!!

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice and water for 20 minutes.
Mix egg, sugar, cornstarch, butter and milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Stir in rice, vanilla and spices.

title: old fashion macaroni 'n' cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni in six cups boiling, salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water. Meanwhile, melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring 1 minute. Gradually whisk in milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, whisking.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and whisk in cheeses until melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter, stir in bread crumbs and sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugars; beat until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture along with cherries, oats and coconut.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place whole cherry in center.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions.
Add the 3 jars spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
In order, layer lasagna noodles (uncooked), sauce mixture, 1/2 the cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat again.
Top with 1 more layer of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Refrigerate until time to bake and noodles are soft.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fruit ice
directions: Melt sugar in water and cool. Add bananas, orange and lemon juice and pineapple and freeze, stirring frequently. A wonderfully light and refreshing dessert.

title: potato flake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with 1/3 cup oleo.
Rinse chicken in cold water; roll in potato flakes. Place in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour, turning once halfway through baking.

title: quick 7 easy beans
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onions until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly. Simmer uncovered stirring occasionally for 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed or pour into ungreased 2 quart casserole. Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and mash with a fork.
Drain as well as you can. Mix soup, sour cream, onions and pimentos together, then stir in squash.
Pour into a casserole dish that you have sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, salt and soda. Add fruit cocktail, eggs and vanilla.
Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325°
for 40 minutes.

title: special chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream the butter and mix in the sugars. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Blend together flour, oatmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt, then add to butter mixture. Gradually add chocolate chips and broken pieces of Hershey's candy bars to mixture.
Drop spoonfuls of cookie dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; let stand 1/2 hour. Dip chicken in buttermilk and shake in plastic bag filled with wheat germ, mashed potato flakes, garlic powder and paprika. Place chicken in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until chicken is brown and tender.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin maple pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Coat a 2 1/2-quart baking dish with nonstick spray.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Mix all together; mix mayonnaise lightly and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: bacon and cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
Keeps for days.

title: ham casserole
directions: Put thawed hash browns in bottom of baking dish; cover with broccoli.
Mix mushroom soup with milk and mayonnaise; mix well. Add ham to that and pour on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and lay chicken on top of rice.
Mix the 2 cans of soup together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle soup mix on top and pour water around the edges.
Cover with 2 layers of aluminum foil, sealing edges over pan.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: beef and cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave on FULL power 3 to 4 minutes, stirring often, until cheese is melted and dip is hot. Serve warm with chips or crackers. (Especially good with Fritos.)

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls on a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Press to form solid crust.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool. While crust is cooling, mix together Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Hidden Valley (dry) mix until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Mix vegetables together and spread over cream mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Press lightly.
Cut and serve.

title: corn flake squares
directions: Put sugar and syrup in large pan and bring to a boil.
Let it boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat and stir in peanut butter, then mix in corn flakes and spread out on cookie sheet.
Cut into squares when cooled.
Put in a cup of raisins and/or chopped nuts, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and rice.
Melt margarine in a large pan.
Add celery and saute.
After celery has cooked 5 minutes, add onions. Cook until tender.
Combine broccoli, rice, soups and cheese in the pan with the celery and onions.
Mix well until cheese is melted. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.

title: janet's fabulous bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a large baking dish. Mix all ingredients very well (by hand).
Place in dish and bake. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: hot and spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Pour ingredients into large saucepan; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins(my great-grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cut together margarine and sugar with pastry blender.
Add egg and Raisin Bran; cut this in also, let set.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate the dry ingredients with milk.
Blend or cut in carefully; do not stir.
After mixing, put in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, magarine, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart dish.
Place in microwave and bring to a boil.
Cook on High speed for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Mix well.

title: easy ole chicken
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam.
Put over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often. Add tomato sauce, corn, green chilies, chili powder and onion powder.
Bring to a boil.
