Reduce heat to medium/low and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. To serve, spoon over tortilla chips and top with cheese.

title: easy crab salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender and drain.
While pasta is cooling, cut green onions and celery into very small pieces.
Chunk crab meat into bite-size pieces.
Mix pasta shells, onions, celery and crab together.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise and mix thoroughly. Sprinkle with black pepper.
Refrigerate until cool and serve with crackers.
Recipe is easily doubled or tripled for large groups.

title: fritos pie
directions: Layer starting with Fritos, chili, cheese and onion.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used, finishing with a layer of cheese. Do this in an ovenproof bowl. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put peaches and juice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mix over peaches.
Dribble melted margarine over cake mix; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: mama rek's pickles
directions: Bring water, sugar and salt to a boil.
Add vinegar.
Then add cucumbers and cook until they turn somewhat yellow in color.
Put pieces of dill stem in bottom of jars.
Add pickles and juice.
Put dill flower on top and seal.
Let age 3 weeks.
(Adjust liquid according to amount of cucumbers available.
After one batch, add more vinegar, sugar and salt to water in pot.)

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add strawberries and gelatin; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into 3 lightly greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with strawberry frosting.
Yields three 8-inch layers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian style zucchini
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, zucchini and herbs.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until zucchini is tender.
Place zucchini on serving dish and season to taste with salt and pepper. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Place strips of bread on cookie sheet and cook to 200° for 1 hour.
Melt peanut butter, oil and brown sugar over low heat. After mixture is melted, dip bread strips into mixture and then roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: baked caramel corn(southern living, 1982)
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, honey and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into large roaster pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican chicken delight
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces. Cut tortillas in 4 or 5 pieces.
Layer in pan as follows: tortillas, chicken, cheese and onion.
Mix soups, broth and green chilies.
Pour over layer and repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Good to fix ahead of time, then bake.)

title: chicken marsala
directions: Flatten chicken pieces between waxed paper with rolling pin or wooden mallet.
Combine egg and milk.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour.
Repeat to use all egg and flour.
Refrigerate 2 hours and proceed to next step. Heat oil and butter.
Brown chicken.
Remove to plate.
Saute green pepper, onion, mushrooms and garlic in skillet until barely tender. Remove to plate.
Add wine and broth.
Boil, uncovered, 10 minutes, to reduce liquid.
Return chicken and vegetables to pan and heat.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and margarine. Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top of this.
Put pieces of butter on top.
Add more water if needed.
Bake at 325° about 2 hours uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tostados
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, chili powder, oregano leaves and cumin; mix well.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Sprinkle over first mixture.
Bake until bubbly and light brown in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Melt German chocolate; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients except chips.
Fold in melted chocolate and chocolate chips. Pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine berries, eggs and oil.
Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon into berry mixture.
Mix well.
Mix pecans and 1/2 cup flour.
Add to bread mixture.
Mix well. Grease and flour loaf pans (2 large or 3 medium or 4 small).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Thaw ice cream.
Put ice cream in pie crust.
Fix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Put on top of pie.
Slice strawberries and place on top.
Freeze until firm.
Slice and serve.

title: muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add the rice, stirring well, then combine with the milk and eggs which have been mixed together.
Lastly, stir in the melted butter.
Turn into well-greased muffin tins and bake in a quick oven (425°) for 25 minutes.
This receipt makes 12 muffins.

title: monkey biscuits
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine ingredients in bowl. Take pieces of biscuits and toss around in sugar mixture.
Drop in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar mixture on top of pieces.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks of butter and 1 cup sugar in pan.
Bring to boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over sugared biscuit pieces.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Dump out of pan immediately onto plate.

title: spaghetti squash boats
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out seeds. Place squash, cut side down, in a baking dish. Fill pan with hot water to a depth of 1/2 inch. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30-40 minutes or until tender. When cool enough to handle, scoop out the squash, separating strands with a fork;

set shells and squash aside. In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion and bell pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender; drain. Add mushrooms, garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add squash; mix well. Cook, uncovered, until liquid has evaporated, about 10 minutes. Fill shells; place in a shallow baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; return to the oven for 5 or until cheese is melted. Don't know what the carb content is but I do know it's low carb.

title: hi ho cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on Hi Ho crackers.
Top with second cracker.
Yields about 80 sandwiches.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: roast pork tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork, in dish or Ziploc bag. Mix to blend.
Add pork and cover tightly.
Marinate 2 hours or overnight.
Roast at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently with marinade.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into wet mixture.
Do not beat but blend well.
Stir in nuts and spoon batter into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, salt and yeast together.
Let stand until yeast is dissolved.
Melt butter.
Add yeast mixture to flour. Add butter and eggs.
Beat about 5 minutes.
Put some flour into a pan; make a well. Pour dough into the pan; knead well.
Let rise. Cut into pieces.
Roll out; butter well.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
You may add raisins also; roll up.
Cut into 1-inch rolls.
Put into buttered pan; let rise.
Bake in 400° oven until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Top with crumbs mixed in butter and place in a large casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: linguine with broccoli and bay scallops
directions: Cut one bunch broccoli into flowerets or 1/4-inch slices. Blanch for 2 minutes in boiling salted water, then drain and refresh in cold water.
Cook linguine until al dente, then drain and toss with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and keep warm.
Heat 1/4 cup butter.
Add minced garlic.
Saute and then add the broccoli; heat through.
Add bay scallops, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Spoon over the pasta and sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Cook cakes in frypan in just enough fat to prevent sticking, until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.
Also delicious if broiled.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Wash, peel and slice cucumbers very thin.
Place in glass bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Allow to stand for an hour or so.
Dry the cucumbers on a paper towel.
Stir together the remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.

title: angel hair pasta with lemon and garlic
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Put olive oil and garlic in pan and cook over medium heat until garlic starts to brown. Remove pan from heat and add wine.
Return to heat.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until wine is reduced by half.
Stir in lemon juice and tomato.
Remove pan from heat.
Cook pasta in water until done (30 seconds to 1 minute).
Drain pasta and put in warm serving bowl. Add the basil, Parmesan cheese and black pepper, along with the tomato mixture.
Toss and serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Contains 4.1 grams fat and 291 calories per serving.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except ground round.
Cover and bring to boil.
Add ground round; mix well.
Return to heat and cook for 35 to 40 minutes on medium-high.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dutch butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar and cream again.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix together, add remaining ingredients and mix again. Roll in one-inch balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.	Heat large iron skillet and grease.
Pour in 2/3 of
batter.
Cover
top
with grated cheese.
Add balance of batter.
Bake
40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Wash, peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Drain. Slice Cheddar cheese.
Arrange carrots and cheese in layers in a buttered two-quart casserole. Make white sauce, using butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Flavor sauce with mustard and celery salt (may add onion flavoring, too).
Pour white sauce over carrots and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or more.

title: cool devil's food cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan per directions on box.
Frost and cover with entire container of Cool Whip.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: meal in a dish
directions: In 5-quart kettle, brown meat, cooking until crumbly.
Add onion and cook until this is translucent.
Stir in water, bouillon cubes, vegetables, bay leaf and basil, pasta and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
Just before serving, remove bay leaf.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together except walnuts.
Form into log and cover with walnuts.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes until done; remove from water. Peel and mash potatoes; add margarine and sweeten to taste.
Add enough milk until pudding texture.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: fruit and nut cookies
directions: Beat first five ingredients together.
Sift together next two ingredients and add.
Mix in last two ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 14 minutes.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: Sprinkle sugar over strawberries; set aside at least 2 hours. Drain strawberries, reserving juice.
Set strawberries aside. There should be 3/4 cup juice; if not, add white grape juice to make this amount.
In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over strawberry juice; allow it to soften for 5 minutes.
Heat slowly to melt, stirring constantly.
Place lemon, zest, gelatin and juice in a blender until smooth.
Add half the berries; blend until smooth.
Mash remaining berries; fold into pureed mixture. Process in an ice cream maker until slightly thickened.
Add beaten egg whites; process until thick.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Makes 2 pints.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix corns, sour cream, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add Jiffy corn bread mix and mix again.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm in the middle.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels into pieces.
Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Pour over pretzels and mix.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: newburg sauce
directions: Precook lobster, crab or shrimp.
Separate eggs and beat yolks and add cream to beaten yolks.
Set aside.
Melt butter and add dry ingredients, mixing until a smooth texture.
Add egg yolk and cream mix, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and texture is smooth.
Add sherry in same manner.
Add meat.
Serves approximately 4 to 6.

title: easy crab dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine crabmeat, cream cheese and butter. Heat and mix thoroughly.
Transfer to hot chafing dish.
Serve with large size corn chips.
If you want to jazz it up a bit, add Old Bay seafood seasoning to taste.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and then mix together with soup and cheese.
Cover top with a layer of Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown onion, bacon and hamburger. Drain liquid from all beans. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jo jo potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and drain. Beat egg, milk and baking powder together and roll potatoes in batter. Mix together flour and seasoned salt (enough to turn color of flour), then roll potatoes in flour mixture. Deep-fry.

title: currant scones
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Using pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in currants.
Add buttermilk to mixture all at once, stirring with a fork to make soft, slightly sticky dough.

title: granny annie's famous meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and press in pan.
Top with brown sugar and ketchup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soya chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Mix well and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight to blend flavors. Just before serving, add the chow mein noodles.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; cover.
Process at mix until well blended.
Bake on lightly greased griddle until nicely brown. Turn only once.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix drained green beans and soup in casserole.
Add 1/2 soup can of water with chopped onions, mushrooms, garlic and 1 can onion rings.
Stir and put remaining can of onion rings over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo.
Add nuts and butter flavoring.
Stir until nuts are coated.
In another bowl combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Do not beat.
Add chocolate mixture and blend carefully.
Fill paper cupcake cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender (should be crisp). When done, drain and rinse in cold water. Alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and rings of sliced onions in casserole-type dish.
Make marinade of remaining ingredients. Heat until well blended. Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: nana morgan's blueberry cake(excellent; melts in your mouth)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream shortening with sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Fold in egg whites, vanilla and blueberries.
Put in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (for glass pan, 325° oven for 50 minutes).
You may sprinkle sugar on it for topping.

title: cheese bread
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt in a saucepan.
Heat until shortening melts.
Cool mixture to 105° to 115°.
Add milk mixture, egg and 2 cups flour to yeast mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Add soup and corn. Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Sift
together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, vanilla, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Pour into
an 8	x
8-inch
pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Cook noodles.
Combine hamburger, onion, noodles and remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put garlic, red pepper and dill seeds in the bottom of each pint jar.
Pack tight with tender okra.
Then boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Put 1/2 teaspoon dill seed on top of each jar. Add boiling mixture to jars.
Seal jars.
Let stand 2 weeks before opening.
Best to heat jars before filling.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Let marinate 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli until almost tender. Drain liquid. Follow microwave instructions on package.

title: whole wheat nut bread
directions: Combine milk and honey.
Add 1 cup of flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add remaining flour and nuts to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in very slow oven at 275° for 2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: joe's champagne punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in the lemon juice.
Combine ingredients, except strawberries and champagne.
Just before serving, add the strawberries and champagne.
Serves 20.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining mix, 1 egg and oil; mix well.
Will be crumbly.
Press mixture into bottom and up the sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, slowly add milk and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 65 minutes, or until center is firm.
Cool; cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate with chocolate shavings, cherries, etc.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine cookie crumbs and margarine; press firmly on the bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In small bowl toss 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips evenly over top.
Bake 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched lightly in the center.
Cool to room temperature and then chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Gradually add milks, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir about one-fourth of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, continuously stirring, 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and next two ingredients.
Spoon mixture into already cooked pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Place cranberries on the bottom of a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar and nuts over the top.
In a bowl, beat eggs, 1 cup sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and shortening; beat well. Pour over cranberry mixture.
Bake at 325° for
1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve beef cubes in boiling water and cool.
Add softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes thick and boil until almost soft but not mushy. Drain water and set potatoes aside, covered.
Slice peppers and onions.
Lightly saute in a little oil.
Mix vinegar, chili sauce and spices.
Mix potatoes, onions and peppers and blend with vinegar/spice mixture.
Top with bacon bits.

title: florida lime pie
directions: Mix well milk, lime juice, zest and egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in baked pie crust for 30 minutes at 250° until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Reserving 2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Combine nuts with reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool and chill.
Cut into bars.

title: dill dip
directions: Triple batch will use 1 (16 ounce) sour cream and 1 (16 ounce) mayonnaise.
Good for a party!

title: calico (baked) beans
directions: Drain all beans but pork and beans.
Mix all ingredients in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Top with uncooked Polish sausage and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(Top with cooked bacon last 5 minutes.) Yield:
10 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add crushed wafers and milk.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Bake in well greased tube pan at 275° for 2 hours or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp; drain and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, stirring until cream cheese is in tiny pieces.
Fold in shrimp. Serve chilled.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails attached, if desired. Saute shrimp with melted butter, oil, white wine, lemon juice, garlic powder, 1 tablespoon minced parsley, Old Bay seasoning and salt in a large skillet over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes on each side.
(Shrimp are done when they turn pink and are firm.) Sprinkle with parsley before serving. Bring to table and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased 9X13 inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove casserole from refrigerator. Let sit at room temperature for 30 minutes. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until casserole reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and
cut
eggplant
in
chunks; boil until tender. Drain and
mash
with
butter.
Add
slightly
beaten
egg and onion, grated
cheese, milk and seasonings.
Mix well and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until firm and lightly browned on top.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: gluten free pastry
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Stir into a ball.
Knead a few seconds.
Roll out between sheets of wax paper or foil.
Use as with regular pie crust.
Before baking, brush the top crust with a slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
This gives a golden brown, very pretty crust.
You can also brush the top crust with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
If you fail to do either, your crust will be quite pallid.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes for single crust.

title: party seafood dip
directions: Simmer onion and garlic in butter until golden.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and cream gradually, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add grated cheese (don't get fancy, just Kraft slices work best) and sherry.
This can be done early in the day.
When ready to serve, add shrimp and crab and cook for five to ten minutes until the crab is cooked and the mixture is heated through but not too hot.
You may need to thin with more milk or add more sherry.

title: gourmet chicken bits
directions: Cut chicken into nugget size.
Combine crumbs, cheese, salt and herbs.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: grandma's butter pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake in oven at 350° until set.
Then at 300°. Use egg whites for meringue.

title: stuffed cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Stuff before baking with date, olive or pecan.

title: chocolate malt cheesecake
directions: Stir ingredients well, pat in bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: chocolate covered raisins
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and corn syrup in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in powdered sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Drop by half teaspoons into waxed paper.
Chill and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: tapioca orange jello
directions: Mix in large saucepan juice from mandarin oranges with enough water for 3 cups.
Add jello and tapioca pudding mix.
Bring to boil.
Cool completely.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Pour in glass dish and refrigerate.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well.
Shape in long roll.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and slice thin.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and coconut cream.
Then stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 2 unbaked shells for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie pan that has been greased and floured. This will make its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown onion in oleo.
Add soup, cheese, celery and milk.
Stir in broccoli.
Make layer of rice, broccoli and cheese. Bake in greased casserole at 325° for 1 hour or until broccoli is tender.

title: grilled peaches with raspberry puree
directions: Combine raspberries and lemon juice in an electric blender. Process until smooth.
Strain raspberry puree; discard seed.
Cover and chill.
Cut 1 (18 x 18-inch) sheet heavy-duty aluminum foil. Place peach halves, cut side up on foil.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon evenly into center of each peach half.
Sprinkle with rum flavoring and dot with margarine.
Fold foil over peaches, loosely seal.
Place each peach bundle on rack and cook 15 minutes or until peaches are heated.
To serve, spoon 2 tablespoons raspberry puree over each chilled peach half.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds and minced onion.
Add mayonnaise, light cream and lemon peel.
Toss together lightly. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dog supper
directions: Cook frankfurters 5 minutes in boiling water to cover; drain. Place frankfurters in buns and arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Top each with mustard and catsup and sprinkle evenly with onion.
Spoon on chili, spreading to cover frankfurters.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 additional minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Fill loaf pan 1/2 full.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until done.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In skillet, saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Blend in milk.
Cool slightly.
Stir in salmon and pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons bread crumbs; mix thoroughly.
Shape into patties or logs.
Roll in remaining crumbs.
Saute in remaining margarine until evenly browned on all sides.
Yields 3 servings.

title: cherry fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a small bowl, whisk flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cherries.
In another small bowl, whisk together buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour mixture just until well blended.
Spread in prepared pan; sprinkle with reserved sugar and bake in uppper third of oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center is covered with very moist crumbs.
Cool completely in pan before cutting.
Makes 16 bars.
A fat-free recipe.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and crushed pineapple.
Reserve juice and add water to make 2 cups.
Bring juices to a boil.
Add black-cherry and raspberry jello.
Stir to dissolve.
Stir in cola (12 ounce cold Coke).
Chill until slightly thick.
Combine chopped celery, chopped pecans and coconut (optional).
Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add to fruit mixture.
Fold cream cheese-fruit mixture into gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: alfajores argentinos
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients in a bowl, except sugar.
Mix the butter with the sugar in another bowl.
Add the egg yolks to the sugar mixture and mix.
Incorporate the dry ingredients.
Stretch the dough and cut with a tiny glass.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil whole chicken (if not using broth).
Make large skillet of cornbread; don't let get real brown, just until done.
In large bowl, mix onion, celery, 2 slices of loaf bread, 1 tablespoon shortening, seasoning and 2 cups broth and let set until it is all moist.
Crumble cornbread in bowl, stirring constantly.
Add eggs fast so as not to cook with cornbread.
Add a little bread at a time.
Taste before bread is added to oven.
Add salt and pepper. Add margarine to pan mixture.
Bake at 500° in preheated oven until brown.

title: chilighetti
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat with garlic and onion.
Pour off grease.
Stir in tomatoes and chili; simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl, mix Cheddar cheese and spaghetti.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix with meat; top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: austrian style fried chicken
directions: Quarter each chicken, discarding the first two joints of the wings.
Remove the breast bones and ribs and remove the skin and any fat.
Have ready in 3 wide, shallow bowls the flour, the eggs and the bread crumbs.
Dredge the chicken in the flour, shake off the excess; dip in the egg and the bread crumbs, shaking off the excess.
Arrange the chicken on a baking sheet lined with wax paper and chill it, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
The chicken may be prepared up to this point 1 day in advance and kept uncovered and chilled.

title: john's salad(heavenly hash)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over hot water; cool slightly.
Add fruit cocktail with syrup.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream.
Add fruit mixture.
Pour in decorative bowl.
Dot top with cherries.
Freeze until firm.

title: pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix spices in sour cream.
Layer ingredients in a pan in this order: cream cheese, sour cream mixed with spices, pizza sauce, pepperoni, pepper and onions.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add butter.
Mix together egg and milk and add to above.
Press in sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Combine all fruits in a large bowl and set aside.
In a smaller bowl combine pudding, milk and orange juice.
Beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: ranch chicken breasts
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine and then place chicken breasts in skillet over medium heat.
Pour 1/2 of the dressing over chicken; allow breasts to brown slightly before turning over. Coat the other side of chicken with remaining dressing.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.

title: marrilee's fish appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Thin mixture with milk as needed; heat through.
This recipe may be used as a main course over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch morsels together over hot, but not boiling water, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Spread evenly over Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Mix all liquids and spices.
Mix beef and liquids.
Cook until almost done.
Add vegetables and finish cooking.

title: chuck wagon mac casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner according to package.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown meat and drain.
In oil saute celery, green pepper and onion until tender.
Add to meat and layer on top of macaroni and cheese.
Layer corn.
Salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes and tomato paste over top.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple glaze for ham
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
May be used as glaze while cooking ham or may be put on individual servings.
This would be good used on other meats as well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to mixture with 1 1/4 cups sweet milk.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: teddy boy(creamy yogurt drink with apricot)
directions: Put fruit into a glass.
Top with sparkling mineral water and decorate with lime slice.
Add ice cubes before serving.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: In a bag, combine flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add chicken pieces and shake.
Pour 4 tablespoons of butter into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in pan, turning pieces to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie(simply delicious -- easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients, then dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Fill ready-made crust or your own. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 375° until pie is done, about 35 more minutes.

title: chinese lamb chops(serves four)
directions: Mix mustard, soy sauce, brown gravy sauce and oyster sauce in a 1-quart mixing bowl.
Put lamb chops into plastic container. Pour sauce mixture over lamb chops and marinate overnight.
Drain and reserve the marinade.
Place lamb chops on grill.
Grill lamb chops to desired doneness.
Approximately 5 minutes before done, brush with reserved marinade.
Serve with rice.

title: stuffed mushroom balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into small size balls and place in 4 1/2-quart cooking pan.
Pour in 2 cans of mushroom soup and 1 can water; mix thoroughly and cook over medium-low heat 30 to 45 minutes or until meat balls are done.
Serve over rice.

title: greens(collards, mustards, turnips)
directions: Boil meat in water while washing greens.
Chop greens and put in boiling water with meat.
Cook for 20 minutes and add remaining seasoning.
Cook for 1 hour, constantly checking to be sure water is above level of greens.
Cook for 20 minutes more or until greens are tender, this time letting water level drop below level of greens.

title: appetizer fruit cup or dessert
directions: Hollow out bread and tear pieces into bite size.
Mix all other ingredients together and put into the hollowed out bread. Arrange pieces around bread.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the flour.
Then mix in flour.
Mix well.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°. Cool before taking out of pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package and drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients to macaroni and toss with dressing.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups. Bring to boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl; add boiling liquid.
Stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.
In a mixing bowl, whip the cream; gradually beat in sugar.
Fold into the gelatin mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: broiled fish steak
directions: Grease broiler pan well and preheat it in broiler.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Place on hot pan.
Combine butter and lemon juice; pour half over fish and broil 3 inches from heat for 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn fish; pour remaining butter mixture on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 6 minutes longer until fish flakes with a fork.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spicy bean soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot oil:
Cook green pepper and onion for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally; stir in soup, chickpeas, beans, water, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve topped with cheese.
Make 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: meat rolls
directions: Cut meat into 3 or 4-inch squares.
Place desired filling in center of each piece.
Roll the meat and tie with string.
Dip rolls in flour.
Heat Fluffo in skillet or Dutch oven and in it brown the rolls on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Remove rolls to serving dish and strain gravy over them.
Sprinkle with parsley. If desired, stir 1/4 cup of cream into gravy.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and egg; bring to a full boil. Add chocolate chips, graham cracker crumbs and coconut, mixing well.

title: veal cutlet parmesan
directions: Dip cutlets in beaten eggs.

Combine with seasonings, then bread crumbs. Fry in olive oil until brown (about 8 minutes). Place cutlets in baking dish. Spread tomato sauce and slices of Mozzarella cheese over them. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat together well all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set and light brown on top.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir yeast, milk, melted shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour together; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Grease bowl.
Put dough in bowl; turn dough over.
Cover; put in warm place.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; cut into rolls.
Put in pan. Cover; let rise 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream
oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one
at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, sifted flour, cinnamon,
allspice, salt
and
soda.
Add
alternately to creamed mixture
with buttermilk.
Add figs and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, 300° for 25 minutes.

title: easy casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Cool, peel and dice.
Make gravy over hamburger with water and cornstarch.
Heat lima beans.
Add potatoes and hamburger mixture.
Mix Bisquick and milk together.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: north coast pork roast
directions: Place roast fat side up on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Rub with mixture of 1/2 teaspoon chili powder, garlic salt and salt. Insert meat thermometer.
Roast at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or 165° on meat thermometer.
Combine catsup, jelly, vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder in small saucepan; simmer for 2 minutes. Brush over roast; sprinkle with corn chips.
Roast 10 to 15 minutes longer or to 170° on meat thermometer.
Remove to serving platter. Let stand 10 minutes.
Add enough water to pan drippings including corn chips to measure 1 cup.
Bring to boil and serve with roast. Yield:
8 servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding.
When thick fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers and pudding two times, ending with graham crackers on top. Squeeze chocolate syrup over crackers.
Let soften overnight.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and poppy seed in melted oleo. (Save some for top.) Cover bottom of baking dish. Combine chicken soup, chicken and sour cream. Spread over cracker layer. Top with remaining cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix
tomato
sauce, vinegar, mustard and sugar; set aside. Mix
meat,
egg, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper; mix well and stir in
tomato mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, shortening and salt together.
Add yeast to mixture.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour, mixing thoroughly to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until dough doubles (about 2 hours).
Turn onto floured board again.
Shape as desired.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Peel and cut enough potatoes into 1/4-inch slices to measure 8 cups.
Combine potato slices, onions and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover. Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 cake pans. Mix all ingredients and pour into pans. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: #1 easy ice cream
directions: Use French vanilla for vanilla or fresh fruit flavors. Use chocolate fudge for chocolate.

title: cold cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onion and peppers in food chopper.
Put cucumbers, onion and peppers in colander and press out all the liquid.
Remove from colander to mixing bowl and add your salt, pepper and vinegar.
Put in pint jars and screw lid on as tight as possible.
Do not cook.
This is real sour; relish is good on hot dogs or any meat.

title: wedding cake icing
directions: Mix Crisco with 1/2 of powdered sugar, then beat.
Mix very well before adding water, then add rest of powdered sugar.
This is very important!
Four recipes will do a 6 layer wedding cake.

title: cheesy charlies
directions: Combine the ingredients, except the buns, in a medium-sized bowl.
Spread mixture on buttered hamburger buns.
Place, open-faced, in a cold broiler.
Broil for 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked ziti (pasta)
directions: Saute the onion in the oil in a saucepan until tender.
Add the tomato paste, tomato sauce, water, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, evaporated milk, and peanut butter for 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Add and beat vanilla flavoring, marshmallow cream, and peanut butter. Pour into 9 x 9 inch pan.

title: hot dog and green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans as label directs, but only for 3 minutes; drain.
In same saucepan, blend margarine and flour; slowly stir in milk, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook until thickened.
Add hot dogs and green beans; pour into casserole.
Top with bread cubes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon butterfly rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 1 cup flour.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat milk and 1/2 cup butter or margarine (1 stick) until very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter or margarine does not need to melt.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts (pecans).

title: microwave pecan or almond pralines
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large glass bowl; cover and cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir, cover and cook on High for 4 minutes longer.
Add vanilla and pecan pieces.
Stir and cover.
Cook on High for 90 seconds.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by teaspoon onto cooling pad (several sheets of newspaper with waxed paper on top).

title: orange balls
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add orange juice and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls into coconut flakes.

title: baked ham and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine honey, butter, green pepper, soy sauce and mustard.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly to mix well.
Turn into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered about 1 hour.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in a mixing bowl with the boiling water.
Add bananas, strawberries and pecans.
Pour half of the mixture into a long baking dish. Chill until firm, then spread with sour cream. Spoon remaining jello over sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water and set aside.
Put flour and seasoning in brown paper bag.
Put the chicken thighs in.
Shake vigorously to thoroughly coat each piece of chicken.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all together except marshmallows, just stir these in.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and mix cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; blend until smooth.
Stir in cake flour. Blend mixture until doughy texture.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and press with a fork.
Bake at 375°.
Makes approximately 36.

title: chicken linguica bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water.
Place in 1 large cooking bag or covered casserole dish.
Add water and tie bag.
Poke several holes in top of bag.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serve with vegetable of choice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa, margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, flour, salt, coconut and pecans; mix well.
Bake in 9 x 15-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wakefield holiday dip
directions: Thaw fish.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in lemon juice, chopped onions and garlic powder.
Fold in crabmeat.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: senior citizen salad
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Just before serving, add 1 sliced banana.

title: brisket
directions: Line pan with foil.
Pour in liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Lay brisket over mixture in pan (lean side down). Sprinkle with garlic salt and onion salt; cover pan tightly with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator the next day.
Remove foil and pour barbecue sauce on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: slim creamy cool cucumber soup
directions: Put
cucumbers,
scallions, dill, parsley and yogurt in blender.
Puree.
Add
remaining
ingredients;
blend
again. Serve chilled
with a sprig of fresh dill floating on top or a thin slice of cucumber.
Makes 8 servings, 85 calories each.

title: rutabagas and pork
directions: Peel and chop the rutabaga.
Cover with water.
Place pork chops on top and boil until the "bagas" and pork chops are real tender.
Add Corn Meal Dumplings to thicken the soup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in small pot; cook until medium brown.
Add sugar and Karo and cook until thick; cool.
Beat eggs and add salt and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Place chopped pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: helen's dutch apple dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Toss mixture into apples. Mix oats and 1/2 cup flour.
Pour apple mixture into 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle oat and flour mixture over apples. Melt butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Pound artichokes upside down until leaves begin to open up. Rinse well and shake off excess water.
Cut stems off and core a little hole in the bottom of the artichoke.

title: bread pudding
directions: Lightly grease 2 (6-ounce) custard cups.
Place half of bread crumbs
in	each
of the two cups.	Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon raisins.

title: nancy's green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy pot.
Bring to a boil, turn down and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil to soft stage when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix and stir until thickened.
Pour on greased platter.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: armenian vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into medium size pieces into large bowl. Add oil and tomato sauce.
Mix together and pour into large baking pan and cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste every 20 minutes.
If it gets dry, add more sauce.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Beat with a mixer, then add oil and poppy seed.
Blend well.
Store in a jar with the onion.

title: coffee cake
directions: Break egg into a measuring cup.
Fill with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add
4 tablespoons of melted butter and vanilla and beat.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Soak beans in 2 cups water.
Cook carrots, celery and onion until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add beans and pasta.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of the sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Stir until mounds on spoon.
Cook 10 minutes longer. Stir occasionally.
Mix egg yolks with sugar; blend in some of the hot mixture and mix well.
Pour this into the rest of the hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: homemade stickers
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until gelatin is dissolved completely.
Use a paint brush to paint mixture on the backs of the papers that you want to use for stickers.

title: jello-ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve the package of jello in boiling water.
Add softened ice cream and stir well.
Let set until thickened.
Stir in celery and pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding with milk until thick.
Combine pudding, cake mix and egg in a bowl.
Beat by hand until mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix nuts with morsels and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Add salad dressing (Wish-Bone, etc.), Salad Supreme, tomatoes (chopped fine) and green pepper.
Mix in large bowl.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes with the toasted bread crumbs and stir in onion, salt and sugar.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot through.

title: "fried" chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse and dry chicken.
Pour buttermilk into pan; on wax paper combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then into flour.
Spray baking sheet with Pam. Place chicken on baking sheet, meaty side down.
Drizzle oil evenly over pieces.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes longer or until juices are clear when pricked with fork.

title: party punch
directions: Mix until frozen items are melted.
Add ice cubes before serving.
Serves 40.

title: forty-niners
directions: Mix well in electric mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Stir in mayonnaise, water and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chive dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: pizza macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain off all fat.
Combine beef with onion and macaroni in skillet.
Add pizza sauce and tomato sauce and seasonings to taste; mix and blend well.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, any amounts; top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange sliced pepperoni, green pepper strips on top just as you would a pizza.
Bake in a 350° oven until thoroughly heated. Glass dish, 25 minutes; Metal dish, 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: snackeroons
directions: Mix the ingredients with fork until a dough forms.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Yields about 36.

title: braised sirloin tips-american heart
directions: Cut 3/4-inch cubes; use loin or hind quarter of the deer. Marinate in the "Game Tame Allergo" sauce overnight.
Drain well. Wrap the pieces of meat with 1/2 strip of bacon on each piece and place on bamboo skewers.
Cook on grill and serve hot or bake, slicing onion on top, at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole - chinese style
directions: Layer browned beef, thawed peas and celery. Mix milk, onion, pepper and salt in soup. Pour over top of casserole. Top with noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until thoroughly hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put above in oblong baking dish.
Stir in 1 cup water and 1-1/2 cups Minute rice.
Lay 4 or 5 chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1-1/2 hours then 1/2 hour uncovered until brown.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Boil together the 4 tablespoons sugar and the water for 5 minutes.
Mix the margarine, Crisco and egg, then add the water-sugar mixture and enough powdered sugar to thicken.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Break pretzels into small pieces.
Mix butter and pretzels in a 9x13 baking dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.
Spread cream cheese on pretzel mixture.

title: venison in gravy with sausage
directions: Salt venison and brown in hot oil.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion, bacon, carrot, celery and parsley to pan drippings.
Saute until carrot is half cooked; add flour, tomato, sage, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Return meat to gravy.
Add wine and enough water to cover the meat.
Add tightly fitting lid and simmer until meat is tender.
Remove venison, strain the gravy and return meat to pan. Add sausages that have been sliced in rounds and bring to a boil. Serve with dumplings.
Serves 8.

title: pueblo bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; add pinch of sugar.
Mix melted lard or oil, salt and yeast in large bowl.

Alternately add flour and water, a little at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition, kneading in last of flour until dough is very smooth. Shape in ball and let rise, covered with damp cloth, in large greased bowl until doubled in bulk.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix salt, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, vinegar and sugar.
Cook over low heat for a few minutes until dissolved.
Let cool.
Pack jars with cucumbers and onions; pour mixture over and tighten lids.
Place in refrigerator and serve when desired.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with mallet to about 1/4 inch.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: prune cake
directions: Boil mixture until it forms a soft ball.

title: seven-fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the lime juice, water and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add nectarines and banana; toss to coat. In a 2 1/2 qt. Glass bowl, combine the remaining fruits. Add nectarine mixture; stir gently. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yield: 8-10 servings.

title: instant ice cream
directions: Place cream and sugar in food processor bowl.
Blend for 1 minute.
Through the feed tube, add frozen fruit, a few pieces at a time.
Process until smooth.
An ice cream will form.
Serve immediately, garnished with cookies or fresh fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased casserole (or 9-inch square pan). Sprinkle with water and lemon juice.
Spoon flour (not sifted) into measuring cup, level off and pour into a bowl.
Add sugar and cinnamon to flour and stir until well blended.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Spoon evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with cream, if desired.

title: cranberry yum yum
directions: Freeze cranberries.
Grind and add the marshmallows and sugar. Chill several hours.
Add pineapple, nuts and whipped cream. Chill until ready to serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes, pepper, onion, soup and milk.
Put butter pats on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese last 30 minutes.

title: adelle payne's holiday relish
directions: Wash and sort cranberries, removing stems and soft berries. Peel, core and quarter apples.
Cut oranges and lemon into quarters, removing seeds and pithy centers.
Put cranberries, oranges and lemon through food chopper, using the medium blade. For the apples, use a coarser blade.
Add sugar, stirring until all ingredients are evenly mixed.
Chill before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and packet of seasoned sauce mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat tomatoes and water to boiling; stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.
You can substitute 1/2 pound ground beef, browned and drained, or 1/2 pound sausage.

title: janet's holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix
Cool
Whip, cottage cheese and Jell-O well.
Drain cans of	fruit.	Add
to
mixture.
Add bananas and nuts; mix well. Set in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: fast chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice per package directions.
Steam chicken or reheat leftover chicken; heat gravy.
Layer generous serving of rice. Top with chicken portion and cover with gravy, as desired.
Serve with vegetable or salad.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Put all beans and sauce in slow cooker and cook 1 hour on low and 1 hour on high.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Add to beans before starting slow cooker.

title: herb cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: artichokes and beans
directions: In a heavy frypan, saute scallions and onion in oil over very low heat.
When transparent but not browned, add artichokes, beans, salt, pepper, lemon juice, butter and carrot.
Cook over lowest possible heat (with cover on) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: malted milk nut dainty
directions: Dissolve the malted milk in 1 cup of the water, then add the sugar and remaining water which has been heated to boiling.
Cook to 240° or soft ball stage, then add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture begins to grain.
Then pour into buttered pan.

title: "best" blue cheese dip
directions: Mix and let stand several hours or overnight.
If not enough bite, add a few drops of vinegar.
If too "bitey" add a little sugar.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Wash meat and cut to fit in crock-pot.
Pour over soup mixed with seasoning.
Lay onions on top and cook until tender.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Make a batter of sugar, flour and milk.
Melt margarine in baking dish, then add peaches.
Pour batter over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and let cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box and add Eagle Brand milk and 1 box Cool Whip to pudding; mix well.
After cake is cool, cut into squares.
Start layering ingredients in punch bowl, starting with cake, pineapple, pie filling, banana slices, Cool Whip and pecans; then end with pudding mixture.
Then start over with cake again and repeat until you reach the top of punch bowl, then cover top with Cool Whip and top with a few pecans and cherries.

title: wonder soup(no calories)
directions: Cut vegetables in medium pieces and boil, covered, with water for 10 minutes.
Turn on low and simmer until soft.
Season with any herb seasoning or dry soup mix.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons for each cup of water.

title: corn cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans.
Boil corn for 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Cool and then cut off the cob, scraping all the juice.
Set aside.
Mix corn meal, flour, eggs, milk and water, then add corn and stir well.
Fill muffin pans half full or 3/4 full depending on size of pan.
This recipe will make 24 to 36 muffins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Top with butter, if desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and blend well. Mix cocoa and food coloring together.
Add vinegar and mix well.
Add this to egg and sugar mixture.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in horseradish and dry mustard.
Heat through.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 100 balls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and make into loaf.
Place in pan with 1-inch water.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots 20 minutes in salt water and drain.
Mix carrots, peppers and onion.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer 1/2 of each into dish.
Repeat.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Wash and drain 1 1/2 or 2 cups fresh strawberries. Sweeten to taste. Pour on bottom of baked pie shell. Cook cream mixture or pudding mix in double boiler until thickened. Cool. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over berries. Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks. Add sugar to taste. Put meringue on top and brown lightly.

title: one cup fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit thoroughly.
Mix and chill.
Maraschino cherries may be added.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Dot with 1/2 stick margarine.
Crush 1 tube Ritz crackers and put on top.
Bake about 30 minutes or until it begins to bubble.

title: hidden sloppy joe
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in catsup, mustard and soup.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Spread 2 cups of batter on bottom of pan and 2 inches up sides and center of pan.
Spoon meat mix on that.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoon 1/2 inch apart.
Bake 25 minutes.
Invert.
Serves 6.

title: cornmeal crusted rockfish(serves 2 people)
directions: Cut rockfish into 2 even portions.
Lay on plate and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat each side with cornmeal and let sit while preparing relish.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef in a Dutch oven, then add all the other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover pan and cook for an hour or a little more.
Makes 3 quarts; 6 or 7 bowls.
Can be frozen in serving sizes.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Cut up apricots and soak 30 minutes in hot water. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add apricots to dry ingredients and nuts, orange juice, egg and butter. Put in greased and floured pan (I only spray my foil pans with Pam). Makes 1 large loaf or 3 (1-pound) loaf pans. Let rise for 15 minutes. Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in bread comes out clean.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and add all other ingredients.
Cook on top of stove at medium heat until heated.

title: party punch
directions: Combine.
Place in a a large punch bowl with ice.
This is excellent for birthday parties or potlucks.
For added color, freeze orange or lemon wedges in ice cube trays with water.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Take out and reserve 1 cup cake mix for top.
Mix butter or margarine and eggs together.
Mix with cake mix and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, cocoa, flour, eggs, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cover with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven and melt marshmallows 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate "no bake" cookies
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Then drop on waxed paper.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: old-time chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding broth, then eggs last.
The mixture should be thin enough to stir easily.
If not, add more broth or hot water with 2 tablespoons of butter or oleo.
If too thin, add more bread or cracker crumbs.
Grease a loaf pan and pour dressing into pan.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over cold water in saucepan. Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatine dissolves (4 to 5 minutes). Remove from heat; add ice water. Stir in tomato sauce and sugar. Pour into 4-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Place on lettuce and garnish with cucumber slices.
Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: u.p. state fair bean sandwich
directions: Mix beans, onion and relish.
Toast muffins.
Spoon about 1/4 cup bean mixture on bottom of each muffin.
Broil until beans are hot.
Place slices of cheese on top and broil until cheese melts. Cover with buttered half of muffin.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: *Best when eaten with bananas, strawberries, apples and pineapple.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Mix sugar to water.
Cook until it forms a medium ball in cold water, then add vanilla and some food coloring.
Put on popped corn at once and stir.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat tomato soup to boiling.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Soften gelatin in water.
Add to soup mixture and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add mayo, Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add shrimp, celery and onions.
Pour into lightly greased 6-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Stir drink mix and water until dissolved.
Beat lemonade mixture and ice cream in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed until blended well.
Stir in Cool Whip until smooth and mixed well.
Freeze this mixture until mixture mounds, then spoon into the pie crust.

title: tofu meatless meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and wash tofu thoroughly.
Using fork, mix all ingredients together, except oil and tomato sauce. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes, turning once.
Put meatless meatballs in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce and keep warm until ready to serve.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: old southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: nonalcoholic champagne
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes and let it cool.
Add all other ingredients, except ginger ale and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 50 servings.

title: alpine potato-cheese soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 4-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Saute until tender but not browned.
Stir in potatoes, salt, dry mustard, white pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes until potatoes are very soft.
Press potato mixture through a ricer or a fine sieve into a large bowl.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Heat slowly just to boiling.
Lower heat slightly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately in mugs or refrigerate 3 hours and serve cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix; pour into 3 cake pans and bake according to box directions.

title: cheese ball spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Refrigerate until firm and then form into a ball.
Just before serving, roll in chopped nuts. This is great on Ritz crackers.
Keeps well if wrapped securely in Saran Wrap.

title: south-of-the-border cumin chicken
directions: Place bell pepper mixture in slow cooker; place chicken on top. To the can of stewed tomatoes, add sugar, oregano, 1 teaspoon of the cumin, salt and pepper sauce, stir gently and pour over chicken bell pepper mixture.
Cover and cook on High 4 hours or on low 8 hours or until meat is just beginning to fall off the bone.
Place chicken in a shallow serving bowl.
Add remaining 3/4 teaspoon cumin to tomato mixture and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cilantro and serve with lime wedges.
Serve over cooked rice or with toasted corn tortillas.

title: salad dressing
directions: Bring the sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil, but do not boil.
Remove from heat and add vegetable oil.
Add to tossed salad as desired.
Must be stored in the refrigerator.
Shake well after storing in the refrigerator.
May be kept for up to a month in the refrigerator.

title: delicious stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except mushrooms).
Form into balls or patties, depending on the type of mushrooms you use and stuff into the mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for at least 20 minutes (more for larger mushrooms).

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bake as on box in 3 layers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until mixture is moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup of nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: pepperoni bread (stromboli)
directions: Unroll bread.
Leave 1 inch border, brush the rest with beaten egg. Sprinkle good amount of Parmesan cheese over the bread then sprinkle Mozzarella.
Layer the meat.
Roll up.
Tuck in sides and pinch all seams.
Brush with remaining egg. Bake 350°
for 30 minutes on baking stone.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a pan (9 x 13-inch), place the chicken, that has been taken off the bones.
Combine the cream of chicken soup and the 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth; mix well.
Pour over the chicken.
Spoon the Veg-All over next with the juice.
Combine flour, milk and oil.
Mix together and pour over the Veg-All.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar, then add eggs.
Add milk, a little at a time, then add vanilla.
After mixing, add 7 ounce can or package of coconut.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked apples and cheese
directions: Drain apples and place in large baking dish.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add cheese and flour, stir together and place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake (using whipping cream)
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar,
then add vanilla, lemon and eggs (two
at a time), flour and whipping cream.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in vegetable oil until no longer pink in the center. Remove chicken from skillet and saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic until onions are transparent.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serve over cooked egg noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pepper steak
directions: Select 4 to 5 pound sirloin steak. Rub and press 2 teaspoons cracked or coarsely ground whole black pepper in each side, using the palms of the hand. Let stand at room temperature 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Broil on grill or hibachi over hot coals, 5-inches from coals, 9 to 11 minutes per side for medium doneness. Transfer to platter. Sprinkle with salt. When steak is about done, saute 1/2 cup sliced onions in 1 tablespoon butter and spoon over steak.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Fry the hamburger over medium heat until it's no longer pink. Drain fat and stir in the flour.
Stir the meat and flour mixture until it's lightly browned.
Add the water and stir until the mixture thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over toast for breakfast, lunch or along with some carrot sticks and applesauce for a quick dinner.
Serves 4.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add sherbet just before serving.
Serves 25.

title: water chestnuts 'n bacon
directions: Drain chestnuts, cut in 1/2 and marinate in sugar and soy sauce for 45 minutes.
Wrap 1/3 slice of bacon.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix together in a bowl all the listed ingredients.
Then spread in greased, lightly floured pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 25 minutes.
While still warm, cut into squares.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except half of the cheese and put it on top.
Bake until brown.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Heat all together and taste.
Add more vinegar for sourer taste, more sugar for sweeter.
Served hot over fresh spinach.

title: the best apple crisp
directions: Put apples in greased square pan.
Combine other ingredients in bowl of food processor with blade.
Sprinkle over apples and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried apples
directions: Peel and cut apples in halves, taking out seeds and core, and place in a pan.
Fill hollow place with butter and sprinkle well with sugar and a little cinnamon.
Pour in enough water (do not cover) in a pan so as to cook them well done.
Place pan in oven and bake until apples are brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend all of the ingredients together and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese over the top and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: pot roast indienne
directions: Season meat with salt and lemon juice.
Brown meat on all sides.
Combine garlic, onion, cloves, parsley, cinnamon, bay leaf, puree and sugar.
Add to beef.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Cover and simmer about 3 hours or until tender.
If necessary, add water to keep moist while cooking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole no. 1
directions: Boil, bone and dice chicken.
Mix soup with milk.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ground beef, pork, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, milk, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place half the meat mixture in a 9 X 5 inch microproof loaf pan.
Place the sausage link in center of meat mixture.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Stir together browning sauce and water.
Pour over top of meat loaf.
Cook on HI for 14-18 minutes. 4 servings.
Total cooking time:
14-18 minutes.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1 teaspoon Equal Measure or 2 packets Equal sweetener or 1 tablespoon Equal Spoonful in an 8-inch pie pan; pat evenly on bottom and side of pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandma neddermeyer's apple crunch
directions: Spread sliced apples into buttered baking dish.
Cover with white sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour and brown sugar.
Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad-romania(salata de cartofi)
directions: Wash and boil potatoes, let cool. Slice potatoes very thinly and mix with salt, thin sliced onions, pickle rounds, oil and vinegar. Place in salad bowl and garnish with slices of hard boiled egg. You may add tomato slices if you prefer.

title: easy gravy for dressing
directions: Put in saucepan, heat and serve.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix all together; bake in greased casserole (2-quart) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry chinese chicken salad
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Roll chicken pieces in cornstarch.
Brown chicken quickly.
Sprinkle on garlic powder. Add tomato chunks, chestnuts, mushrooms, celery and green onions. Stir.
Add soy sauce.
Stir.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer and cook 5 to7 minutes.
Lightly toss chicken and vegetable mixture with shredded lettuce.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 eggs, tomato paste, cracker crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ground beef.
Mix together and put half of this in the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2 baking pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut and peel squash and boil until tender. Drain, then mash. Soak bread in milk; mix with squash. Add slightly beaten eggs, chopped onions, salt and pepper. Pour all in casserole. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: marshmallow face
directions: Spread Marshmallow Creme on half a graham cracker, then take two
