marshmallows, place on graham cracker for eyes.
Place a raisin in middle of the marshmallow eyes, then put a raisin on the graham cracker for a nose.
Next, take a slice of the apple and use it for the mouth.
Quick and easy snack for children.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° until done about 2 or 3 hours.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add half to creamed mixture.
Add mincemeat and stir until blended.
Mix remaining flour and nuts together.
Add to other mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: egg bake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use 1 box Brownberry croutons (onion and herbs).
Spread on bottom of pan.
Beat together eggs and 1 cup milk; pour over croutons.
Brown sausage (drain) and spread over mixture.
Add mushrooms, green peppers and onions.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over mixture.
Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or so.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come
to room temperature.	Preheat oven to 325°. Combine by hand the
sausage
and cheese in a bowl; add biscuit mix and blend
thoroughly.	Roll
into small balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: salmon and fettucini alfredo
directions: In a double boiler, melt margarine or butter.
Then add garlic,
heavy
cream,
milk,
cheese and garlic powder.
Stir frequently
with
wire
whisk until heated thoroughly.
As the Alfredo
sauce
is
cooking, boil the fettucini noodles, drain and set
aside.
Grill the salmon fillet (on an outdoor grill if possible, or broil in oven).
When sauce is done, toss into fettucini.
When fillet is done, cut into bite-size pieces and toss that into fettucini also.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Hand mix.
Pour in greased loaf tin. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: orange crush drink
directions: Combine
first
ingredients in blender until smooth. Add 10 whole
ice
cubes and blend until ice is dissolved and smooth. Makes 4 large glasses.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until very light.
Add well beaten yolks of eggs, milk and flour, beating well all the time. Fold in the whites of eggs. Add flavoring, then stir in the baking powder. Bake in a 375° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill cranberry juice and ginger ale.
Mix lemonade with 6 cans of water.
Combine ingredients in order listed.
Serves 35 punch cups.
Freeze a mold of pink ice the day before to add beauty to this summer punch.

title: shepherd's pie(servings:  10)
directions: Brown meat using salt, pepper and garlic.
Do not overcook. Prepare brown gravy mix per directions.
Steam peas and carrots until slightly firm.
Combine meat, vegetables and gravy in
9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mash boiled potatoes, seasoned and whip until very smooth.
Spread mashed potatoes on top of casserole. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until potatoes start to brown.
Suggested Wine:
Merlot or Guiness extra stout.

title: korean hamburger patties
directions: Chop bean sprouts into 1/2-inch lengths.
Squeeze out excess water.
Set aside.
Squeeze tofu with cheesecloth to remove water. In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Make patties using 1/4 cup mixture for each patty.
(Recipe makes 14 patties.) Fry in skillet with a little oil.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter until golden brown.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and tomato sauce.
Add wine, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, stirring until mixed.

title: quick meal
directions: Open can Chef Boyardee and heat according to directions.
Drain Vienna sausage.
Serve.

title: rotisserie dressing
directions: Mix with electric mixer and chill several hours.
Serve over any green or tossed salad.

title: cold raspberry soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat raspberries, Port and cinnamon sticks to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes.
In measuring cup, mix cornstarch with water slowly. Stir into soup; cook until thickened, stirring.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, remove cinnamon sticks.

title: chunky vegetable dip
directions: Prepare beets for cooking.
Wash; leave a little top and roots on beets.
Let boil until tender.
Wash, cool and clean off tops and roots.

title: mother's uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk on low.
Mix all dry ingredients. Pour melted marshmallows on dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pack in buttered loaf pan.
Refrigerate. (This will last for weeks in refrigerator.
Freezes well.)

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Beat eggs in a bowl until fluffy.
Add cooking oil, sugar and defrosted strawberries.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt into a mixing bowl; add strawberry mixture and mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, then turn out on pans and cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.
This bread slices best when chilled.
May be sliced and warmed to serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: the best shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a large baking sheet with 1 tablespoon of softened butter.
Beat 1 pound butter and cup of sugar together at high speed; then beat in flour, one cup at a time.
Beat until smooth.
(You might have to use your hands.)
On floured board, roll out dough to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut rectangles, triangles or Christmas cookie cutter
shapes, etc..
Prick all over with tines of fork.
Bake 22 to 27 minutes until firm and lightly browned.
Cool on cake racks.
Will keep for 2 or 3 weeks in covered jars.

title: sausage roll
directions: Roll out biscuit dough on floured board to 1/2-inch or less in a square.
Spread uncooked sausage (room temperature) evenly over dough.
Roll dough (jelly roll style) into 2-inches in diameter. Refrigerate.

title: pea-filled onion baskets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove centers of onions and chop. Place onion halves in a small baking pan and bake 10 minutes. Combine chopped onions, oregano, peas, mushrooms, butter and red pepper and fill onion cavities.
Cover with foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika before serving.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Shred cheddar cheese. Break up sausage into small bits.
Mix sausage, cheese, biscuit mix, and milk with large spoon. Using tablespoon, spoon out small amounts of biscuit mix onto ungreased baking pan, approx. 1 to 2 inches apart.
Bake at 450° on center rack until lightly golden brown.

title: cherry cheesecake miniatures
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line muffin tins with cupcake liners and place vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Fill 2/3 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Let cool.
Top with about 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.	Grease	bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 28 minutes.	(Don't overbake.)

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except cloves, cinnamon and salt in percolator.
Place cloves, cinnamon and salt in basket.
Allow to go through perk cycle.
Serve piping hot.
Yields 10 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add 1/2 each of the flour and milk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add remainder of milk and flour.
Place in well-greased cake pan, dusted with flour.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Increase heat to 350° and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: the ruby slipper cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except jello.
Pour 1/4 batter into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and sprinkle with part of the dry jello, then part of batter and jello ending with batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine ingredients, except for cheese and toast rounds. Spread on toast rounds.
Top each with 1/4 slice of processed cheese.
Heat on ungreased baking sheet for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: crystallized pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers. Soak in 2 gallons water with 2 cups lime 24 hours. Wash and put in 2 gallons water with small box of alum for 24 hours. Wash and soak in 2 gallons water with small box ginger for 6 hours. Do not wash. Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar and 3 teaspoons pickling spice.
Let stand in syrup 4 hours. Boil 1 hour and put in sterilized jars.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with fork and roll out.
Lay in pan and trim.
Fill.
Lay top crust on; pinch and bake.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk together first, then the rest.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.

title: gluten choplets
directions: Lentils need no soaking.
Bring to a boil 3 cups of salted water and slowly add 1 cup dry lentils so as to not disturb boiling point.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.
If cooked lentils need to be drained, save the liquid to serve as a base for soup, gravy or stew.
One cup dry lentils yields 2 cups cooked.

title: laura's sweet potatoes
directions: Make syrup with water potatoes were cooked in.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: clouds at sunrise(dessert)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until frothy, add cream of tartar then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a well-buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbrown.
Cool on rack.
Whip the cream and spread over top. Spoon pie filling over cream.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: cheese cinnamon toast
directions: Put butter on one side of bread.
Let the butter melt.
Then turn over.
Put cheese on the other side of the bread.
Let the cheese melt.
Then put the cinoman on the toast and eat it.

title: eastern star chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in lots of water (no livers, gizzards or skin). Remove chicken and add celery.
When tender, remove celery and add spaghetti, salt and pepper.
Cook onions, garlic and peppers in butter; simmer 25 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, cheese, bay leaf and olives.

title: bruce fryfogle
directions: Grease a skillet with corn oil.
Heat slowly and stir ingredients, except bacon and eggs.
Add bacon and cook until done (remove from mixture).
Add fresh eggs to mixture and coat with mixture until done.
Place eggs on plate and sprinkle with remaining onions.

title: jalapeno-cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: microwave raisin sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and cook an additional 2 minutes.

title: turkey-sage chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large pan over medium heat until crisp. Remove to paper towel to drain. Add onions to pan and saute 5 minutes or until tender. Add potatoes, milk, broth, soup and 2 tablespoons of sage. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes. Add turkey, bacon and remaining tablespoon sage. Simmer until heated through, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: master biscuit mix
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, cutting shortening into dry ingredients using a pastry tool or 2 knives until it resembles corn meal.
Put in plastic bag.
It will keep in fridge up to 6 months.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil all ingredients, except flour and soda, for 5 minutes. Let cool and add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour.

title: betty wright's punch
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour hot water over top and mix.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Freeze at least 24 hours before serving.
Make ahead for unexpected guests and holidays.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Bake and crumble corn bread.
Chop ham into small cubes.
Mash or cut up tomatoes.
Add drained peas, corn, ham and corn bread; mix well.
Partially cook bacon.

title: garden noodle salad
directions: Boil noodles until done, approximate time 3 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Cut lettuce, cut garlic and cut onions.
Cut tomato wedge style.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add seasoning packets.
Toss as a regular salad.
Serves 4 to 5. Serve chilled with any salad dressing desired.

title: easy bean dip
directions: Layer first four ingredients and heat until bubbling in oven or microwave.
Add avocado and sour cream.
Sprinkle with green onions and black olives.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
As you continue to beat with mixer, gradually add sugar (do not pour all in at once).
Add eggs one at a time.
In another bowl, mix flour and baking powder. Add to creamed ingredients alternating with milk.
Stir in extracts.
Pour in greased and floured (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In large bowl, combine onion soup with water.
Add beef; mix thoroughly.
In skillet, brown mixture; stir in sauce.
In two 3-quart oblong baking dishes, spoon sauce to cover bottom. Alternately layer noodles, cheese and sauce, forming three layers. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 lasagnas.
Great idea is to freeze one and eat it later!

title: scallops a la king
directions: Melt butter in frying pan; add the green pepper, chopped fine and the mushrooms, chopped.
Stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the flour and salt and cook until frothy.
Add the milk and stir until thickened.
In separate bowl, pour boiling water over scallops and let stand for 5 minutes.
Put sauce in double boiler over hot (but not boiling) water.
Add drained scallops.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Serve on toast or between split biscuits.

title: taters
directions: Quarter unpared potatoes.
Brush with mixture 3 times during baking.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate quickies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place oil and chocolate in saucepan over low heat. Stir until chocolate is melted.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add flour mixture to chocolate mixture gradually, mixing well after each addition. Drop dough by teaspoon into powdered sugar. Coat well.
Shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat with mixer.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in diced zucchini.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Put sugar and milk on to boil.
Chop dates and add soda.
Let cook slowly until balls form in cold water.
Remove from heat. Let set awhile.
Put butter and vanilla in next and beat until it thickens.
Add cherries and pecans into a damp cloth and roll.

title: hannah's molasses cookies
directions: Mix ginger, cinnamon, salt and flour together.
Melt shortening and beat in sugar, vanilla and egg.
Dissolve soda in hot water; add to shortening along with molasses.
Slowly blend in flour; mix for very soft dough.
Chill well.
Roll out on floured board or pastry sheet with just enough flour to keep from sticking, rolling 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with 3 inch round cutter.
Sprinkle sugar on top; bake on foil (greased) on cookie sheet in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
They should still be a little soft but done.
Store in covered container, possibly with apple slice.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed, creaming butter and sugar well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake in a 325° oven 20 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again before serving.
Yields about 30 balls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Cream shortening, white and brown sugar.
Add peanut butter and eggs; stir well.
Add flour to mixture.
Mix to a stiff batter.
Add vanilla.
Shape into walnut-sized balls and crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 or 9 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
In a large ovenproof or microwave dish, layer cooked ground beef, sliced cheese and tomato soup so that the pasta and ingredients are covered with soup.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Or microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Serves 4.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together ingredients and place in ice cream freezer.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Chop onion and green pepper and saute in butter or margarine.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese to the mixture.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Combine squash and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke-chili dip
directions: Layer the following in	an
8 x 12-inch baking dish the following in the
order
given:
artichoke hearts (drained and chopped), green chili
peppers (chopped), thin layer of mayonnaise and grated	Monterey
Jack	cheese.
Heat
until
cheese melts for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mash figs.
Add sugar and jello.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while still hot.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until it thickens.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: In small saucepan melt butter and blend in cocoa.
Set aside to cool.

title: quick spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Arrange artichoke halves in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except the bread crumbs and butter.
Pour over artichokes, cover with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves six.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream sit at room temperature to soften.
Crumble cookies in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Spoon softened ice cream over the cookie crumbs.
Break up the candy bars and place on top of ice cream.
Drizzle ice cream topping on top.
Place into freezer. Serve when frozen.

title: chocolate cherry trifle dessert
directions: Note:
Prepare cake as directed on the box.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini, onion and green pepper.
Add salt.
Let stand until syrup is made.
Rinse with cold water and drain.

title: buttermilk fried chicken and biscuits
directions: Place chicken into bowl.
Pour buttermilk over; marinate 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Add alternately with milk to batter; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Boil applesauce, shortening and sugar for 5 minutes.
Let stand overnight or cold.
In large bowl, put chopped fruit and nuts.
Mix flour, soda and spices; put on top of fruit mixture.
Pour cold applesauce mixture over all dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake in greased and lined pans at 250° for 2 1/2 hours, or until done. Fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in sifter.
To this mixture, add shortening as for pie dough and mix.
Add enough milk to make soft dough like biscuits.
Drop about half of mixture in greased baking dish.
Cut apples as for pie; add sugar and cinnamon to apples and mix.
Place apples on top of dough, then put the rest of the dough over the apples in small bits.
Bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Bring water and orange juice to a boil.
Add pudding mix. Bring to a full boil for a few seconds, stirring until clear.
Add Jell-O.
Stir and then cool well.
Fold in Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Chill until ready to serve.
Can also use fresh oranges, marshmallows and nuts.

title: mint pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
With pastry blender, cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles cornmeal.
Add egg white and mint extract and stir until well mixed.
Shape dough into 2 balls and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut one ball into 12 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into an 11 inch rope. Place on cookie sheet and twist into pretzel shape.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes and remove to wire rack to cool.
May be frosted with a powdered sugar (use mint extract) frosting.

title: sugarless date-nut squares
directions: Simmer fruit in water for 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine; cool mixture.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in cooled fruit mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half.
Arrange around edge and center of dish.
Combine 1 teaspoon sugar and cinammon and sprinkle over cobbler.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and butter, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Spoon into a greased and floured medium size muffin pan, filling each muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade, condensed milk and Cool Whip thoroughly. Pour into the prepared pie shell and refrigerate for several hours.

title: dorito dip
directions: Mix together; refrigerate for 12 to 16 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet, adding salt and pepper.
Also add onion, if desired, and cook with meat until tender.
Place meat in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish (sprayed with Pam).
Cover meat mixture with stewed tomatoes and sweet corn.
Spoon prepared muffin mixture on top of corn.
Bake at 350° until muffin mix is done.

title: green chili pie
directions: Put peppers on bottom of pie dish.
Spread cheese over peppers.
Beat eggs with milk and pour on top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350° or seven or eight minutes in a microwave. Serve on crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls for hush puppies. Deep fry.
For fritters, pan-fry.

title: snow on the mountain salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese and cottage cheese; mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, chopped cherries, pineapple and marshmallows; mix well.
Pour into quart mold and refrigerate several hours.
Serve from mold.

title: carrot salad
directions: Scrape the carrot for your child and then grind.
Put all the ingredients out and let them assemble their salad and eat.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients (save 1 cup cheese).
Sprinkle top with 1 cup cheese. Pour on top 1 stick butter, melted.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of oblong pan.
Sprinkle on top:
grated cheese, chopped green onions, green peppers, chopped tomatoes and chopped sliced black olives.

title: newlywed casserole
directions: Remove papers and quarter tamales.
In large casserole, combine beans, chili, corn and tamales.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package instructions, omitting salt. Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until blended and smooth but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid (vegetable juice and milk), stirring slowly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese (which has been cut in small pieces).
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine with cooked, drained spinach.
This may be served immediately or put into a casserole and topped with buttered bread crumbs.
The flavor is improved if allowed to set overnight in refrigerator.
This casserole can be frozen; bake in moderate oven until bread crumbs are browned and dish is bubbling hot.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll bread dough out well.
Put cheeses and pepperoni on dough.
Roll tight and wet edges.
Pinch to secure.
Put in oven with light on for 1 hour to rise.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300° until lightly browned.

title: fudge-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Add oatmeal and blend thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Do not bake!

title: tuna fish macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in pot with water.
Put tuna in a bowl.
Add cut up pickles and cooked macaroni.
Add mayonanise; stir it, then eat it.

title: red salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans(big batch)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Combine all ingredients in a large greased roaster.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours or 450° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 25.

title: how to make brown sugar
directions: Mix by hand, it's faster.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Garnish with bacon and parsley flakes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie nouveau(serves 4)
directions: Cook carrots in 1 cup stock with rosemary (boil 4 to 5 minutes).
Drain and discard rosemary (reserve liquid).
Blanch peas (30 seconds).
Boil onion (10 minutes).
Make roux with butter and flour.
Add carrot/chicken stock, simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Whisk until thick and add remaining stock and rosemary.
Combine all vegetables in sauce.
Serve in cooled puff pastry.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine and put half in large mold.
Chill and spread with sour cream.
Add remaining jello and chill.

title: german butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese toast(for people who have to watch their fat intake.)
directions: Spread margarine on bread and put a slice of cheese on top. Spread mustard lightly over the cheese and sprinkle lightly with celery seed.
Toast in broiler oven until bread starts to brown.

title: unusual chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken and red pepper in a large bowl.
Steam the broccoli for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add it to the chicken and mix it in gently.
Mix in the crumbled bacon.

title: soy chicken
directions: In a wok or Dutch oven, mix sugar and soy sauce; heat to boiling.
Add chicken, baste with sauce and return to boiling. Lower heat to medium, cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes, turning and basting chicken every 5 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter and serve sauce at the table.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; dust with flour and a dash of salt.
Brown in butter in a skillet large enough to accommodate all ingredients.
When nicely browned, add mushrooms, onions, garlic and chicken broth.
Cook slowly on low heat, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: polish delights
directions: Brown meats separately; drain well.
Mix together with cheese and seasonings.
Place on 2 packages of party rye bread.
Quick freeze on a cookie sheet, then store in freezer in Ziploc bags. Bake 15 minutes frozen or 8 minutes thawed at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop
shrimp
and mix with other ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with potato chips.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons salmon liquid; flake. Combine cream cheese, liquid smoke flavoring and salmon liquid; blend thoroughly.
Stir in green onion, then fold in salmon. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve as a spread for crackers or Melba toast rounds.
Makes 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift dry ingredients into pumpkin mix and stir well.
Stir in nuts and dates. Put into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lois' chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oats in blender to a fine powder.
In a large bowl, with mixer, cream butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine oatmeal powder, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add oat mixture to butter mixture; beat until blended.
With wooden spoon, stir in chocolate pieces, grated chocolate and nuts.
Place by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Dough needs to be a little stiff, add extra flour if needed. Sprinkle flat surface with flour.
Pour mixture on top.
This can be rolled out or patted out, then cut in strips or cut out and dropped in chicken broth.
Reduce heat; cover with lid.
Stir a couple of times during cooking, but avoid stirring too often.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Add soup, water, pasta and vegetables.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown 6 pork chops.
Spray Pam in large cake pan and place chops in single layer.
Cook 1 cup rice.
Put thick slice of onion on each chop.
Put mound of cooked rice over each onion.
Mix 1 can tomato soup, 1 pint tomatoes and 1 small (6 ounce) can tomato paste.
Pour over chops and rice.
Cover (I use foil).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with sauce every half hour.

title: cold sesame chicken
directions: Blend soy sauce, sugar, vinegar, oils, ginger, pepper flakes and pepper for 10 seconds.
Combine sauce with pasta and chicken. Marinate for 2 hours.
Garnish with green onions.

title: w. v. "mountain mama's" microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave margarine and peanut butter on High for 3 minutes. Stir, then add vanilla.
Add 4 cups powdered sugar and stir well. Press into pan and cut when cool.
(Easy and delicious!)

title: pizza cookie
directions: Line 12 ounce pizza pan with heavy-duty foil; grease.
Cream butter or margarine; gradually add sugar, beating with electric mixer (medium speed).
Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour with baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla extract; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate pieces and 1/4 cup pecans.
Spoon batter into pan to within 1 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with coconut and remaining 1/4 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows and remaining candy pieces on top.
Bake additional 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut in wedges.
Serves 20.

title: pasta vegetable chowder
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse pasta under cold water until cool; drain again.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for about 15 minutes or until tender. Drain well.
Add butter, egg, milk, soup and salt and pepper. Pour into baking dish.
Top with the cornbread dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old south chicken dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread.
Pour chicken stock with melted butter over bread mixture.
Add onions, celery, eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles; drain.
Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in noodles; let cook on top of stove about 10 minutes longer.
Add peas if desired.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add milk, then dry ingredients.
Drop with teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
